  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Jeremiah, the son of Hilkiah, one of the priests who
        were in Anathoth in the land of Benjamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'to whom the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came in the days
        of Josiah the son of Amon, king of Judah, in the thirteenth year of his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Call of Jeremiah'
      title: The Call of Jeremiah
      number: 3
      content: 'It came also in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of
        Judah, and until the end of the eleventh year of Zedekiah, the son of Josiah,
        king of Judah, until the captivity of Jerusalem in the fifth month.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CBefore I formed you in the womb I knew you,and before you
        were born I consecrated you;I appointed you a prophet to the nations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>! Behold, I
        do not know how to speak, for I am only a youth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,\u201CDo not say,
        \u2018I am only a youth\u2019;for to all to whom I send you, you shall go,and
        whatever I command you, you shall speak.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  Do not be afraid of them,  for I am with you to deliver you,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> put out his hand and touched
        my mouth. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,\u201CBehold, I
        have put my words in your mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "See, I have set you this day over nations and over kingdoms,  to
        pluck up and to break down,to destroy and to overthrow,to build and to plant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me, saying,
        \u201CJeremiah, what do you see?\u201D And I said, \u201CI see an almond[[COMMENT(0)]]
        branch.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: sounds like the Hebrew for (compare verse 12)
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CYou have seen
        well, for I am watching over my word to perform it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me a second time,
        saying, \u201CWhat do you see?\u201D And I said, \u201CI see a boiling pot,
        facing away from the north.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201COut of the
        north disaster[[COMMENT(0)]] shall be let loose upon all the inhabitants
        of the land. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: The Hebrew word can mean , , or , depending on the context; so throughout
          Jeremiah
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For behold, I am calling all the tribes of the kingdoms of the north,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and they shall come, and every
        one shall set his throne at the entrance of the gates of Jerusalem, against
        all its walls all around and against all the cities of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I will declare my judgments against them, for all their evil
        in forsaking me. They have made offerings to other gods and worshiped the
        works of their own hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But you, dress yourself for work;[[COMMENT(0)]] arise, and say to
        them everything that I command you. Do not be dismayed by them, lest I dismay
        you before them. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And I, behold, I make you this day a fortified city, an iron pillar,
        and bronze walls, against the whole land, against the kings of Judah, its
        officials, its priests, and the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They will fight against you, but they shall not prevail against you,
        for I am with you, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, to deliver you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Forsakes the '
      title: 'Israel Forsakes the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo and proclaim in the hearing of Jerusalem, Thus says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201CI remember the devotion of your youth,your
        love as a bride,  how you followed me in the wilderness,  in a land not sown.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  Israel was holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  the firstfruits
        of his harvest.  All who ate of it incurred guilt;disaster came upon them,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, O house of Jacob,
        and all the clans of the house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CWhat wrong did
        your fathers find in methat they went far from me,  and went after worthlessness,
        and became worthless?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They did not say, \u2018Where is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>who
        brought us up from the land of Egypt,who led us in the wilderness,in a land
        of deserts and pits,in a land of drought and deep darkness,in a land that
        none passes through,where no man dwells?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  And I brought you into a plentiful landto enjoy its fruits and
        its good things.But when you came in, you defiled my landand made my heritage
        an abomination.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The priests did not say, \u2018Where is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u2019 
        Those who handle the law did not know me;  the shepherds[[COMMENT(0)]] transgressed
        against me;  the prophets prophesied by Baaland went after things that do
        not profit.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTherefore I still contend with you,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        with your children\u2019s children I will contend.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For cross to the coasts of Cyprus and see,or send to Kedar and examine
        with care;see if there has been such a thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Has a nation changed its gods,  even though they are no gods?But
        my people have changed their gloryfor that which does not profit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Be appalled, O heavens, at this;be shocked, be utterly desolate,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for my people have committed two evils:  they have forsaken me,the
        fountain of living waters,and hewed out cisterns for themselves,broken cisterns
        that can hold no water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  \u201CIs Israel a slave? Is he a homeborn servant?Why then has
        he become a prey?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  The lions have roared against him;they have roared loudly.They
        have made his land a waste;his cities are in ruins, without inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover, the men of Memphis and Tahpanhes  have shaved[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the crown of your head.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Have you not brought this upon yourselfby forsaking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,when he led you in the way?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  And now what do you gain by going to Egyptto drink the waters of
        the Nile?  Or what do you gain by going to Assyriato drink the waters of
        the Euphrates?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Your evil will chastise you,and your apostasy will reprove you.Know
        and see that it is evil and bitterfor you to forsake the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God;the fear of me is not in you,declares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFor long ago I broke your yokeand burst your bonds;but you
        said, \u2018I will not serve.\u2019Yes, on every high hilland under every
        green treeyou bowed down like a whore.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Yet I planted you a choice vine,wholly of pure seed.  How then
        have you turned degenerateand become a wild vine?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Though you wash yourself with lyeand use much soap,  the stain of
        your guilt is still before me,declares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  How can you say, \u2018I am not unclean,I have not gone after the
        Baals\u2019?Look at your way in the valley;know what you have done\u2014a
        restless young camel running here and there,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  a wild donkey used to the wilderness,in her heat sniffing the wind!Who
        can restrain her lust?None who seek her need weary themselves;in her month
        they will find her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Keep your feet from going unshodand your throat from thirst.But you
        said, \u2018It is hopeless,  for I have loved foreigners,and after them I
        will go.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAs a thief is shamed when caught,so the house of Israel shall
        be shamed:  they, their kings, their officials,their priests, and their prophets,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "who say to a tree, \u2018You are my father,\u2019and to a stone,
        \u2018You gave me birth.\u2019For they have turned their back to me,and not
        their face.But in the time of their trouble they say,\u2018Arise and save
        us!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But where are your godsthat you made for yourself?Let them arise,
        if they can save you,in your time of trouble;for as many as your citiesare
        your gods, O Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CWhy do you contend with me?You have all transgressed against
        me,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'In vain have I struck your children;they took no correction;  your
        own sword devoured your prophetslike a ravening lion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And you, O generation, behold the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Have
        I been a wilderness to Israel,or a land of thick darkness?Why then do my
        people say, \u2018We are free,we will come no more to you\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  Can a virgin forget her ornaments,or a bride her attire?Yet my
        people have forgotten medays without number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CHow well you direct your courseto seek love!So that even to
        wicked womenyou have taught your ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Also on your skirts is found  the lifeblood of the guiltless poor;you
        did not find them breaking in.Yet in spite of all these things  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "you say, \u2018I am innocent;surely his anger has turned from me.\u2019 
        Behold, I will bring you to judgmentfor saying, \u2018I have not sinned.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: '  How much you go about,changing your way!You shall be put to shame
        by Egyptas you were put to shame by Assyria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: From it too you will come awaywith your hands on your head,for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected those in whom you trust,and you
        will not prosper by them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201CIf[[COMMENT(0)]] a man divorces his wifeand she goes from
        himand becomes another man\u2019s wife,will he return to her?  Would not
        that land be greatly polluted?  You have played the whore with many lovers;and
        would you return to me?declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac; Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Lift up your eyes to the bare heights, and see!Where have you not
        been ravished?  By the waysides you have sat awaiting loverslike an Arab
        in the wilderness.  You have polluted the landwith your vile whoredom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Therefore the showers have been withheld,and the spring rain has
        not come;yet you have the forehead of a whore;you refuse to be ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Have you not just now called to me,\u2018My father, you are the friend
        of my youth\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Faithless Israel Called to Repentance'
      title: Faithless Israel Called to Repentance
      number: 5
      content: "  will he be angry forever,will he be indignant to the end?\u2019Behold,
        you have spoken,but you have done all the evil that you could.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me in the days of King Josiah:
        \u201CHave you seen what she did, that faithless one, Israel, how she went
        up on every high hill and under every green tree, and there played the whore? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I thought, \u2018After she has done all this she will return
        to me,\u2019 but she did not return, and her treacherous sister Judah saw
        it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'She saw that for all the adulteries of that faithless one, Israel,
        I had sent her away with a decree of divorce. Yet her treacherous sister
        Judah did not fear, but she too went and played the whore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Because she took her whoredom lightly, she polluted the land, committing
        adultery with stone and tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Yet for all this her treacherous sister Judah did not return to me
        with her whole heart, but in pretense, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CFaithless Israel
        has shown herself more righteous than treacherous Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Go, and proclaim these words toward the north, and say,  \u201C\u2018Return,
        faithless Israel,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.I will not look
        on you in anger,for I am merciful,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        I will not be angry forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Only acknowledge your guilt,that you rebelled against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your Godand scattered your favors among foreigners under every green tree,and
        that you have not obeyed my voice,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Return, O faithless children,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        for I am your master;I will take you, one from a city and two from a family,and
        I will bring you to Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201C\u2018And I will give you shepherds after my own heart, who
        will feed you with knowledge and understanding. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when you have multiplied and been fruitful in the land, in those
        days, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, they shall no more say, \u201CThe
        ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D It shall not
        come to mind or be remembered or missed; it shall not be made again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'At that time Jerusalem shall be called the throne of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and all nations shall gather to it, to the presence of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in Jerusalem, and they shall no more stubbornly follow their own evil heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In those days the house of Judah shall join the house of Israel,
        and together they shall come from the land of the north to the land that
        I gave your fathers for a heritage.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201C\u2018I said,How I would set you among my sons,and give you
        a pleasant land,a heritage most beautiful of all nations.And I thought you
        would call me, My Father,and would not turn from following me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  Surely, as a treacherous wife leaves her husband,so have you been
        treacherous to me, O house of Israel,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "A voice on the bare heights is heard,  the weeping and pleading of
        Israel\u2019s sonsbecause they have perverted their way;they have forgotten
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  \u201CReturn, O faithless sons;  I will heal your faithlessness.\u201D\u201CBehold,
        we come to you,for you are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Truly the hills are a delusion,the orgies[[COMMENT(0)]] on the mountains. 
        Truly in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our Godis the salvation of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CBut from our youth the shameful thing has devoured all for
        which our fathers labored, their flocks and their herds, their sons and their
        daughters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Let us lie down in our shame, and let our dishonor cover us. For
        we have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, we and our
        fathers, from our youth even to this day, and we have not obeyed the voice
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf you return, O Israel,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        to me you should return.If you remove your detestable things from my presence, 
        and do not waver,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  and if you swear, \u2018As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives,\u2019in
        truth, in justice, and in righteousness,then nations shall bless themselves
        in him,  and in him shall they glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to the men of Judah
        and Jerusalem:  \u201CBreak up your fallow ground,and sow not among thorns.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Disaster from the North'
      title: Disaster from the North
      number: 4
      content: "  Circumcise yourselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;remove
        the foreskin of your hearts,O men of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem; 
        lest my wrath go forth like fire,and burn with none to quench it,  because
        of the evil of your deeds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Declare in Judah, and proclaim in Jerusalem, and say,  \u201CBlow
        the trumpet through the land;cry aloud and say,  \u2018Assemble, and let
        us gointo the fortified cities!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Raise a standard toward Zion,flee for safety, stay not,for I bring
        disaster from the north,  and great destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  A lion has gone up from his thicket,a destroyer of nations has
        set out;he has gone out from his placeto make your land a waste;your cities
        will be ruins  without inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For this put on sackcloth,lament and wail,for the fierce anger of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>has not turned back from us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIn that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, courage
        shall fail both king and officials. The priests shall be appalled and the
        prophets astounded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then I said, \u201CAh, Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, surely you
        have utterly deceived this people and Jerusalem, saying, \u2018It shall be
        well with you,\u2019 whereas the sword has reached their very life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "At that time it will be said to this people and to Jerusalem, \u201CA
        hot wind from the bare heights in the desert toward the daughter of my people,
        not to winnow or cleanse, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "a wind too full for this comes for me. Now it is I who speak in judgment
        upon them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Behold, he comes up like clouds;  his chariots like the whirlwind;his
        horses are swifter than eagles\u2014woe to us, for we are ruined!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'O Jerusalem, wash your heart from evil,that you may be saved.How
        long shall your wicked thoughtslodge within you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For a voice declares from Danand proclaims trouble from Mount Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Warn the nations that he is coming;announce to Jerusalem,\u201CBesiegers
        come from a distant land;they shout against the cities of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Like keepers of a field are they against her all around,because she
        has rebelled against me,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Anguish over Judah\u2019s Desolation"
      title: "Anguish over Judah\u2019s Desolation"
      number: 18
      content: "Your ways and your deedshave brought this upon you.This is your doom,
        and it is bitter;it has reached your very heart.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  My anguish, my anguish! I writhe in pain!Oh the walls of my heart!My
        heart is beating wildly;I cannot keep silent,for I hear the sound of the
        trumpet,the alarm of war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Crash follows hard on crash;the whole land is laid waste.  Suddenly
        my tents are laid waste,my curtains in a moment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'How long must I see the standardand hear the sound of the trumpet?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor my people are foolish;they know me not;they are stupid
        children;they have no understanding.  They are \u2018wise\u2019\u2014in doing
        evil!But how to do good they know not.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I looked on the earth, and behold, it was without form and void; 
        and to the heavens, and they had no light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I looked on the mountains, and behold, they were quaking,and all
        the hills moved to and fro.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  I looked, and behold, there was no man,and all the birds of the
        air had fled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I looked, and behold, the fruitful land was a desert,and all its
        cities were laid in ruinsbefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, before his
        fierce anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CThe whole land
        shall be a desolation; yet I will not make a full end.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  \u201CFor this the earth shall mourn,  and the heavens above be
        dark;for I have spoken; I have purposed;  I have not relented, nor will I
        turn back.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'At the noise of horseman and archerevery city takes to flight;they
        enter thickets; they climb among rocks;all the cities are forsaken,and no
        man dwells in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And you, O desolate one,what do you mean that you dress in scarlet, 
        that you adorn yourself with ornaments of gold,  that you enlarge your eyes
        with paint?In vain you beautify yourself.  Your lovers despise you;they seek
        your life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For I heard a cry as of a woman in labor,anguish as of one giving
        birth to her first child,the cry of the daughter of Zion gasping for breath, 
        stretching out her hands,\u201CWoe is me! I am fainting before murderers.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem Refused to Repent'
      title: Jerusalem Refused to Repent
      number: 1
      content: '    Run to and fro through the streets of Jerusalem,look and take
        note!Search her squares to see  if you can find a man,one who does justiceand
        seeks truth,  that I may pardon her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  Though they say, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives,\u201D 
        yet they swear falsely.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, do not your eyes look for truth? 
        You have struck them down,but they felt no anguish;you have consumed them,but
        they refused to take correction.  They have made their faces harder than
        rock;they have refused to repent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said, \u201CThese are only the poor;they have no sense;  for
        they do not know the way of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the justice of
        their God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I will go to the greatand will speak to them,for they know the way
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the justice of their God.\u201D  But they
        all alike had broken the yoke;they had burst the bonds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore a lion from the forest shall strike them down;a wolf from
        the desert shall devastate them.  A leopard is watching their cities;everyone
        who goes out of them shall be torn in pieces,because their transgressions
        are many,their apostasies are great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CHow can I pardon you?Your children have forsaken me  and
        have sworn by those who are no gods.  When I fed them to the full,  they
        committed adultery  and trooped to the houses of whores.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They were well-fed, lusty stallions,  each neighing for his neighbor\u2019s
        wife.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Shall I not punish them for these things?declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;and
        shall I not avenge myselfon a nation such as this?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CGo up through her vine rows and destroy,  but make not a
        full end;strip away her branches,for they are not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  For the house of Israel and the house of Judahhave been utterly
        treacherous to me,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They have spoken falsely of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and have
        said, \u2018He will do nothing;  no disaster will come upon us,  nor shall
        we see sword or famine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The  Proclaims Judgment'
      title: The  Proclaims Judgment
      number: 13
      content: "The prophets will become wind;the word is not in them.Thus shall
        it be done to them!\u2019\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of hosts:\u201CBecause
        you have spoken this word,behold, I am making my words in your mouth a fire,and
        this people wood, and the fire shall consume them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Behold, I am bringing against youa nation from afar, O house of
        Israel,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.It is an enduring nation;it
        is an ancient nation,a nation whose language you do not know,  nor can you
        understand what they say.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Their quiver is like an open tomb;they are all mighty warriors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  They shall eat up your harvest and your food;they shall eat up
        your sons and your daughters;they shall eat up your flocks and your herds;they
        shall eat up your vines and your fig trees;your fortified cities in which
        you trustthey shall beat down with the sword.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut even in those days, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        I will not make a full end of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And when your people say, \u2018Why has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God done all these things to us?\u2019 you shall say to them, \u2018As
        you have forsaken me and served foreign gods in your land, so you shall serve
        foreigners in a land that is not yours.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Declare this in the house of Jacob;proclaim it in Judah:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CHear this, O foolish and senseless people,  who have eyes,
        but see not,who have ears, but hear not.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Do you not fear me? declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Do
        you not tremble before me?I placed the sand as the boundary for the sea,a
        perpetual barrier that it cannot pass;though the waves toss, they cannot
        prevail;though they roar, they cannot pass over it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  But this people has a stubborn and rebellious heart;they have turned
        aside and gone away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They do not say in their hearts,\u2018Let us fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God,  who gives the rain in its season,the autumn rain and the spring
        rain,and keeps for us  the weeks appointed for the harvest.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Your iniquities have turned these away,and your sins have kept
        good from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For wicked men are found among my people;  they lurk like fowlers
        lying in wait.[[COMMENT(0)]]  They set a trap;they catch men.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:26 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Like a cage full of birds,their houses are full of deceit;therefore
        they have become great and rich;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  they have grown fat and sleek.They know no bounds in deeds of evil; 
        they judge not with justicethe cause of the fatherless, to make it prosper,and
        they do not defend the rights of the needy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  Shall I not punish them for these things?declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        shall I not avenge myselfon a nation such as this?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'An appalling and horrible thinghas happened in the land:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  the prophets prophesy falsely,and the priests rule at their direction; 
        my people love to have it so,but what will you do when the end comes?'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Impending Disaster for Jerusalem'
      title: Impending Disaster for Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Flee for safety, O people of Benjamin,from the midst of Jerusalem!Blow
        the trumpet in Tekoa,and raise a signal on Beth-haccherem,for disaster looms
        out of the north,and great destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The lovely and delicately bred I will destroy,  the daughter of Zion.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Shepherds with their flocks shall come against her;  they shall
        pitch their tents around her;they shall pasture, each in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CPrepare war against her;arise, and let us attack at noon!Woe
        to us, for the day declines,for the shadows of evening lengthen!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Arise, and let us attack by nightand destroy her palaces!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:  \u201CCut
        down her trees;  cast up a siege mound against Jerusalem.This is the city
        that must be punished;there is nothing but oppression within her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  As a well keeps its water fresh,so she keeps fresh her evil;  violence
        and destruction are heard within her;sickness and wounds are ever before
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Be warned, O Jerusalem,  lest I turn from you in disgust,lest I make
        you a desolation,an uninhabited land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:  \u201CThey shall
        glean thoroughly as a vinethe remnant of Israel;like a grape gatherer pass
        your hand againover its branches.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  To whom shall I speak and give warning,that they may hear?  Behold,
        their ears are uncircumcised,  they cannot listen;behold, the word of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is to them an object of scorn;they take no pleasure
        in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore I am full of the wrath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        I am weary of holding it in.  \u201CPour it out upon the children in the
        street,and upon the gatherings of young men, also;  both husband and wife
        shall be taken,the elderly and the very aged.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  Their houses shall be turned over to others,their fields and wives
        together,for I will stretch out my handagainst the inhabitants of the land,\u201Ddeclares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CFor from the least to the greatest of them,everyone is greedy
        for unjust gain;and from prophet to priest,everyone deals falsely.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They have healed the wound of my people lightly,saying, \u2018Peace,
        peace,\u2019  when there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  Were they ashamed when they committed abomination?No, they were
        not at all ashamed;they did not know how to blush.Therefore they shall fall
        among those who fall;  at the time that I punish them, they shall be overthrown,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CStand by the roads,
        and look,and ask for the ancient paths,where the good way is; and walk in
        it,  and find rest for your souls.But they said, \u2018We will not walk in
        it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  I set watchmen over you, saying,\u2018Pay attention to the sound
        of the trumpet!\u2019But they said, \u2018We will not pay attention.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore hear, O nations,and know, O congregation, what will happen
        to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hear, O earth; behold, I am bringing disaster upon this people, 
        the fruit of their devices,because they have not paid attention to my words;and
        as for my law, they have rejected it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  What use to me is frankincense that comes from Sheba,or sweet cane
        from a distant land?  Your burnt offerings are not acceptable,nor your sacrifices
        pleasing to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u2018Behold,
        I will lay before this peoplestumbling blocks against which they shall stumble;fathers
        and sons together,neighbor and friend shall perish.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CBehold, a people
        is coming from the north country,a great nation is stirring from the farthest
        parts of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They lay hold on bow and javelin;they are cruel and have no mercy; 
        the sound of them is like the roaring sea;they ride on horses,set in array
        as a man for battle,against you, O daughter of Zion!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'We have heard the report of it;  our hands fall helpless;anguish
        has taken hold of us,  pain as of a woman in labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Go not out into the field,nor walk on the road,for the enemy has
        a sword;  terror is on every side.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'O daughter of my people, put on sackcloth,and roll in ashes;  make
        mourning as for an only son,most bitter lamentation,for suddenly the destroyerwill
        come upon us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI have made you a tester of metals among my people,that you
        may know and test their ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  They are all stubbornly rebellious,  going about with slanders;they
        are bronze and iron;all of them act corruptly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The bellows blow fiercely;the lead is consumed by the fire;  in vain
        the refining goes on,for the wicked are not removed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "  Rejected silver they are called,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has rejected them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Evil in the Land'
      title: Evil in the Land
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CStand in the gate of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        house, and proclaim there this word, and say, Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        all you men of Judah who enter these gates to worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel:
        Amend your ways and your deeds, and I will let you dwell in this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Do not trust in these deceptive words: \u2018This is the temple of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor if you truly amend your ways and your deeds, if you truly
        execute justice one with another, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'if you do not oppress the sojourner, the fatherless, or the widow,
        or shed innocent blood in this place, and if you do not go after other gods
        to your own harm, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then I will let you dwell in this place, in the land that I gave
        of old to your fathers forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBehold, you trust in deceptive words to no avail. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Will you steal, murder, commit adultery, swear falsely, make offerings
        to Baal, and go after other gods that you have not known, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and then come and stand before me in this house, which is called
        by my name, and say, \u2018We are delivered!\u2019\u2014only to go on doing
        all these abominations? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Has this house, which is called by my name, become a den of robbers
        in your eyes? Behold, I myself have seen it, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Go now to my place that was in Shiloh, where I made my name dwell
        at first, and see what I did to it because of the evil of my people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And now, because you have done all these things, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and when I spoke to you persistently you did not listen, and when I called
        you, you did not answer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'therefore I will do to the house that is called by my name, and in
        which you trust, and to the place that I gave to you and to your fathers,
        as I did to Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And I will cast you out of my sight, as I cast out all your kinsmen,
        all the offspring of Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAs for you, do not pray for this people, or lift up a cry or
        prayer for them, and do not intercede with me, for I will not hear you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do you not see what they are doing in the cities of Judah and in
        the streets of Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The children gather wood, the fathers kindle fire, and the women
        knead dough, to make cakes for the queen of heaven. And they pour out drink
        offerings to other gods, to provoke me to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Is it I whom they provoke? declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Is it not themselves, to their own shame? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>: Behold,
        my anger and my wrath will be poured out on this place, upon man and beast,
        upon the trees of the field and the fruit of the ground; it will burn and
        not be quenched.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel:
        \u201CAdd your burnt offerings to your sacrifices, and eat the flesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt, I did
        not speak to your fathers or command them concerning burnt offerings and
        sacrifices. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But this command I gave them: \u2018Obey my voice, and I will be
        your God, and you shall be my people. And walk in all the way that I command
        you, that it may be well with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But they did not obey or incline their ear, but walked in their own
        counsels and the stubbornness of their evil hearts, and went backward and
        not forward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'From the day that your fathers came out of the land of Egypt to this
        day, I have persistently sent all my servants the prophets to them, day after
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Yet they did not listen to me or incline their ear, but stiffened
        their neck. They did worse than their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  \u201CSo you shall speak all these words to them, but they will
        not listen to you. You shall call to them, but they will not answer you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And you shall say to them, \u2018This is the nation that did not
        obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God, and did not
        accept discipline; truth has perished; it is cut off from their lips.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Valley of Slaughter'
      title: The Valley of Slaughter
      number: 29
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Cut off your hair and cast it away;raise a lamentation
        on the bare heights,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected and
        forsakenthe generation of his wrath.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CFor the sons of Judah have done evil in my sight, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They have set their detestable things in
        the house that is called by my name, to defile it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And they have built the high places of Topheth, which is in the Valley
        of the Son of Hinnom, to burn their sons and their daughters in the fire,
        which I did not command, nor did it come into my mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Therefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when it will no more be called Topheth, or the Valley of the Son of Hinnom,
        but the Valley of Slaughter; for they will bury in Topheth, because there
        is no room elsewhere. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the dead bodies of this people will be food for the birds of
        the air, and for the beasts of the earth, and none will frighten them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And I will silence in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem
        the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom
        and the voice of the bride, for the land shall become a waste.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAt that time, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        bones of the kings of Judah, the bones of its officials, the bones of the
        priests, the bones of the prophets, and the bones of the inhabitants of Jerusalem
        shall be brought out of their tombs. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And they shall be spread before the sun and the moon and all the
        host of heaven, which they have loved and served, which they have gone after,
        and which they have sought and worshiped. And they shall not be gathered
        or buried. They shall be as dung on the surface of the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Sin and Treachery'
      title: Sin and Treachery
      number: 3
      content: 'Death shall be preferred to life by all the remnant that remains
        of this evil family in all the places where I have driven them, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou shall say to them, Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: 
        When men fall, do they not rise again?If one turns away, does he not return?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why then has this people turned awayin perpetual backsliding?  They
        hold fast to deceit;they refuse to return.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  I have paid attention and listened,but they have not spoken rightly;no
        man relents of his evil,saying, \u2018What have I done?\u2019Everyone turns
        to his own course,  like a horse plunging headlong into battle.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Even the stork in the heavensknows her times,and the turtledove,
        swallow, and crane[[COMMENT(0)]]keep the time of their coming,  but my people
        know notthe rules of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: 'The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertainOr '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  \u201CHow can you say, \u2018We are wise,and the law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is with us\u2019?But behold, the lying pen of the scribeshas made it into
        a lie.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  The wise men shall be put to shame;they shall be dismayed and taken;behold,
        they have rejected the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,so what wisdom
        is in them?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Therefore I will give their wives to othersand their fields to
        conquerors,because from the least to the greatesteveryone is greedy for unjust
        gain;from prophet to priest,everyone deals falsely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They have healed the wound of my people lightly,saying, \u2018Peace,
        peace,\u2019when there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Were they ashamed when they committed abomination?No, they were not
        at all ashamed;they did not know how to blush.  Therefore they shall fall
        among the fallen;when I punish them, they shall be overthrown,says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When I would gather them, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,there
        are no grapes on the vine,  nor figs on the fig tree;  even the leaves are
        withered,and what I gave them has passed away from them.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:13 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Why do we sit still?  Gather together; let us go into the fortified
        citiesand perish there,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God has doomed
        us to perishand has given us poisoned water to drink,because we have sinned
        against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  We looked for peace, but no good came;for a time of healing, but
        behold, terror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201CThe snorting of their horses is heard from Dan;at the sound
        of the neighing of their stallions  the whole land quakes.They come and devour
        the land and all that fills it,the city and those who dwell in it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jeremiah Grieves for His People'
      title: Jeremiah Grieves for His People
      number: 17
      content: "For behold, I am sending among you serpents,adders that cannot be
        charmed,  and they shall bite you,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'My joy is gone; grief is upon me;[[COMMENT(0)]]  my heart is sick
        within me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:18 '
        content: Compare Septuagint; the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Behold, the cry of the daughter of my peoplefrom the length and breadth
        of the land:\u201CIs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> not in Zion?  Is her
        King not in her?\u201D  \u201CWhy have they provoked me to anger with their
        carved imagesand with their foreign idols?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe harvest is past, the summer is ended,and we are not saved.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the wound of the daughter of my people is my heart wounded; 
        I mourn, and dismay has taken hold on me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Is there no balm in Gilead?Is there no physician there?Why then has
        the health of the daughter of my peoplenot been restored?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]  Oh that my head were waters,and my eyes a fountain
        of tears,that I might weep day and nightfor the slain of the daughter of
        my people!  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: '  Ch 8:23 in Hebrew    '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]] Oh that I had in the deserta travelers\u2019 lodging
        place,that I might leave my peopleand go away from them!For they are all
        adulterers,a company of treacherous men.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: '  Ch 9:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  They bend their tongue like a bow;falsehood and not truth has grown
        strong[[COMMENT(0)]] in the land;for they proceed from evil to evil,  and
        they do not know me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Let everyone beware of his neighbor,and put no trust in any brother,for
        every brother is a deceiver,and every neighbor goes about as a slanderer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Everyone deceives his neighbor,and no one speaks the truth;they have
        taught their tongue to speak lies;they weary themselves committing iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Heaping oppression upon oppression, and deceit upon deceit,  they
        refuse to know me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:\u201CBehold,
        I will refine them and test them,for what else can I do, because of my people?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Their tongue is a deadly arrow;  it speaks deceitfully;with his
        mouth each speaks peace to his neighbor,but in his heart he plans an ambush
        for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Shall I not punish them for these things? declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        shall I not avenge myselfon a nation such as this?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CI will take up weeping and wailing for the mountains,and a
        lamentation for the pastures of the wilderness,  because they are laid waste
        so that no one passes through,and the lowing of cattle is not heard;  both
        the birds of the air and the beastshave fled and are gone.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  I will make Jerusalem a heap of ruins,  a lair of jackals,  and
        I will make the cities of Judah a desolation,without inhabitant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Who is the man so wise that he can understand this? To whom has
        the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoken, that he may declare
        it? Why is the land ruined and laid waste like a wilderness, so that no one
        passes through? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CBecause they have
        forsaken my law that I set before them, and have not obeyed my voice or walked
        in accord with it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but have stubbornly followed their own hearts and have gone after
        the Baals, as their fathers taught them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the
        God of Israel: Behold, I will feed this people with bitter food, and give
        them poisonous water to drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will scatter them among the nations whom neither they nor their
        fathers have known, and I will send the sword after them, until I have consumed
        them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:  \u201CConsider,
        and call for the mourning women to come;send for the skillful women to come;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'let them make haste and raise a wailing over us,  that our eyes may
        run down with tearsand our eyelids flow with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For a sound of wailing is heard from Zion:  \u2018How we are ruined!We
        are utterly shamed,because we have left the land,because they have cast down
        our dwellings.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Hear, O women, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and let
        your ear receive the word of his mouth;teach to your daughters a lament,and
        each to her neighbor a dirge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For death has come up into our windows;it has entered our palaces, 
        cutting off the children from the streetsand the young men from the squares.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Speak: \u201CThus declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  \u2018The
        dead bodies of men shall falllike dung upon the open field,  like sheaves
        after the reaper,and none shall gather them.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CLet not the wise
        man boast in his wisdom, let not the mighty man boast in his might, let not
        the rich man boast in his riches, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "but let him who boasts boast in this, that he understands and knows
        me, that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who practices steadfast love,
        justice, and righteousness in the earth. For in these things I delight, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBehold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when I will punish all those who are circumcised merely in the flesh\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Egypt, Judah, Edom, the sons of Ammon, Moab, and all who dwell in
        the desert who cut the corners of their hair, for all these nations are uncircumcised,
        and all the house of Israel are uncircumcised in heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idols and the Living God'
      title: Idols and the Living God
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear the word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> speaks to you,
        O house of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CLearn not the way
        of the nations,nor be dismayed at the signs of the heavensbecause the nations
        are dismayed at them,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  for the customs of the peoples are vanity.[[COMMENT(0)]]  A tree
        from the forest is cut downand worked with an axe by the hands of a craftsman.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:3 '
        content: 'Or , or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  They decorate it with silver and gold;  they fasten it with hammer
        and nailsso that it cannot move.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Their idols[[COMMENT(0)]] are like scarecrows in a cucumber field,and
        they cannot speak;  they have to be carried,for they cannot walk.Do not be
        afraid of them,  for they cannot do evil,neither is it in them to do good.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  There is none like you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;you are great,
        and your name is great in might.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Who would not fear you, O King of the nations?For this is your
        due;for among all the wise ones of the nationsand in all their kingdomsthere
        is none like you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  They are both stupid and foolish;the instruction of idols is but
        wood!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Beaten silver is brought from Tarshish,and gold from Uphaz.  They
        are the work of the craftsman and of the hands of the goldsmith;their clothing
        is violet and purple;  they are all the work of skilled men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the true God;  he is the
        living God and the everlasting King.At his wrath the earth quakes,and the
        nations cannot endure his indignation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus shall you say to them: \u201CThe gods who did not make the heavens
        and the earth shall perish from the earth and from under the heavens.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:11 '
        content: This verse is in Aramaic
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  It is he who made the earth by his power,  who established the
        world by his wisdom,and by his understanding stretched out the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  When he utters his voice, there is a tumult of waters in the heavens, 
        and he makes the mist rise from the ends of the earth.  He makes lightning
        for the rain,  and he brings forth the wind from his storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Every man is stupid and without knowledge;  every goldsmith is
        put to shame by his idols,for his images are false,  and there is no breath
        in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They are worthless, a work of delusion;at the time of their punishment
        they shall perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Not like these is he who is the portion of Jacob,for he is the one
        who formed all things,  and Israel is the tribe of his inheritance;  the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts is his name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Gather up your bundle from the ground,O you who dwell under siege!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CBehold, I am
        slinging out the inhabitants of the landat this time,  and I will bring distress
        on them,that they may feel it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Woe is me because of my hurt!  My wound is grievous.But I said, \u201CTruly
        this is an affliction,and I must bear it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  My tent is destroyed,and all my cords are broken;my children have
        gone from me,  and they are not;there is no one to spread my tent againand
        to set up my curtains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  For the shepherds are stupidand do not inquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;therefore
        they have not prospered,  and all their flock is scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A voice, a rumor! Behold, it comes!\u2014  a great commotion out
        of the north countryto make the cities of Judah a desolation,  a lair of
        jackals.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  I know, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that the way of man is not
        in himself,that it is not in man who walks to direct his steps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Correct me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, but in justice;not in
        your anger, lest you bring me to nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Pour out your wrath on the nations that know you not,and on the
        peoples that call not on your name,  for they have devoured Jacob;they have
        devoured him and consumed him,and have laid waste his habitation.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Broken Covenant'
      title: The Broken Covenant
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CHear the words of this covenant, and speak to the men of Judah
        and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall say to them, Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel: Cursed be the man who does not hear the words of this
        covenant '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'that I commanded your fathers when I brought them out of the land
        of Egypt, from the iron furnace, saying, Listen to my voice, and do all that
        I command you. So shall you be my people, and I will be your God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "that I may confirm the oath that I swore to your fathers, to give
        them a land flowing with milk and honey, as at this day.\u201D Then I answered,
        \u201CSo be it, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CProclaim all
        these words in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem: Hear
        the words of this covenant and do them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For I solemnly warned your fathers when I brought them up out of
        the land of Egypt, warning them persistently, even to this day, saying, Obey
        my voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Yet they did not obey or incline their ear, but everyone walked in
        the stubbornness of his evil heart. Therefore I brought upon them all the
        words of this covenant, which I commanded them to do, but they did not.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CA conspiracy
        exists among the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They have turned back to the iniquities of their forefathers, who
        refused to hear my words. They have gone after other gods to serve them.
        The house of Israel and the house of Judah have broken my covenant that I
        made with their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Behold, I am
        bringing disaster upon them that they cannot escape. Though they cry to me,
        I will not listen to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the cities of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem will go
        and cry to the gods to whom they make offerings, but they cannot save them
        in the time of their trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For your gods have become as many as your cities, O Judah, and as
        many as the streets of Jerusalem are the altars you have set up to shame,
        altars to make offerings to Baal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore do not pray for this people, or lift up a cry or
        prayer on their behalf, for I will not listen when they call to me in the
        time of their trouble. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'What right has my beloved in my house, when she has done many vile
        deeds? Can even sacrificial flesh avert your doom? Can you then exult? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> once called you \u2018a green olive
        tree, beautiful with good fruit.\u2019 But with the roar of a great tempest
        he will set fire to it, and its branches will be consumed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, who planted you, has decreed
        disaster against you, because of the evil that the house of Israel and the
        house of Judah have done, provoking me to anger by making offerings to Baal.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made it known to me and I knew;then
        you showed me their deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But I was like a gentle lambled to the slaughter.I did not know it
        was against methey devised schemes, saying,\u201CLet us destroy the tree
        with its fruit,  let us cut him off from the land of the living,that his
        name be remembered no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, who judges righteously,who
        tests the heart and the mind,  let me see your vengeance upon them,for to
        you have I committed my cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning the
        men of Anathoth, who seek your life, and say, \u201CDo not prophesy in the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, or you will die by our hand\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: \u201CBehold,
        I will punish them. The young men shall die by the sword, their sons and
        their daughters shall die by famine, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and none of them shall be left. For I will bring disaster upon the
        men of Anathoth, the year of their punishment.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      number: 1
      content: '    Righteous are you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,when I complain
        to you;yet I would plead my case before you.  Why does the way of the wicked
        prosper?Why do all who are treacherous thrive?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You plant them, and they take root;they grow and produce fruit; 
        you are near in their mouthand far from their heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  But you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, know me;  you see me, and
        test my heart toward you.  Pull them out like sheep for the slaughter,and
        set them apart for the day of slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The  Answers Jeremiah'
      title: The  Answers Jeremiah
      number: 4
      content: "  How long will the land mournand the grass of every field wither? 
        For the evil of those who dwell in it  the beasts and the birds are swept
        away,because they said, \u201CHe will not see our latter end.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf you have raced with men on foot, and they have wearied you,how
        will you compete with horses?And if in a safe land you are so trusting,what
        will you do in the thicket of the Jordan?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For even your brothers and the house of your father,  even they have
        dealt treacherously with you;they are in full cry after you;  do not believe
        them,though they speak friendly words to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI have forsaken my house;I have abandoned my heritage;I have
        given the beloved of my soulinto the hands of her enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  My heritage has become to melike a lion in the forest;she has lifted
        up her voice against me;therefore I hate her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Is my heritage to me like a hyena\u2019s lair?Are the birds of prey
        against her all around?Go, assemble all the wild beasts;bring them to devour.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Many shepherds have destroyed my vineyard;  they have trampled down
        my portion;they have made my pleasant portiona desolate wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They have made it a desolation;desolate, it mourns to me.The whole
        land is made desolate,  but no man lays it to heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Upon all the bare heights in the desertdestroyers have come,for the
        sword of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> devoursfrom one end of the land
        to the other;no flesh has peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  They have sown wheat and have reaped thorns;  they have tired themselves
        out but profit nothing.They shall be ashamed of their[[COMMENT(0)]] harvests 
        because of the fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning all my evil
        neighbors who touch the heritage that I have given my people Israel to inherit:
        \u201CBehold, I will pluck them up from their land, and I will pluck up the
        house of Judah from among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And after I have plucked them up, I will again have compassion on
        them, and I will bring them again each to his heritage and each to his land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And it shall come to pass, if they will diligently learn the ways
        of my people, to swear by my name, \u2018As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives,\u2019 even as they taught my people to swear by Baal, then they shall
        be built up in the midst of my people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if any nation will not listen, then I will utterly pluck it up
        and destroy it, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ruined Loincloth'
      title: The Ruined Loincloth
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to me, \u201CGo and buy
        a linen loincloth and put it around your waist, and do not dip it in water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought a loincloth according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and put it around my waist. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me a second
        time, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTake the loincloth that you have bought, which is around your
        waist, and arise, go to the Euphrates and hide it there in a cleft of the
        rock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So I went and hid it by the Euphrates, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And after many days the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CArise,
        go to the Euphrates, and take from there the loincloth that I commanded you
        to hide there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then I went to the Euphrates, and dug, and I took the loincloth from
        the place where I had hidden it. And behold, the loincloth was spoiled; it
        was good for nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Even so will I spoil
        the pride of Judah and the great pride of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This evil people, who refuse to hear my words, who stubbornly follow
        their own heart and have gone after other gods to serve them and worship
        them, shall be like this loincloth, which is good for nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Jars Filled with Wine'
      title: The Jars Filled with Wine
      number: 11
      content: 'For as the loincloth clings to the waist of a man, so I made the
        whole house of Israel and the whole house of Judah cling to me, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that they might be for me a people, a name,
        a praise, and a glory, but they would not listen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou shall speak to them this word: \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, \u201CEvery jar shall be filled with wine.\u201D\u2019
        And they will say to you, \u2018Do we not indeed know that every jar will
        be filled with wine?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        Behold, I will fill with drunkenness all the inhabitants of this land: the
        kings who sit on David\u2019s throne, the priests, the prophets, and all
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Exile Threatened'
      title: Exile Threatened
      number: 14
      content: "And I will dash them one against another, fathers and sons together,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. I will not pity or spare or have
        compassion, that I should not destroy them.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Hear and give ear; be not proud,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God  before
        he brings darkness,before your feet stumbleon the twilight mountains,and
        while you look for lighthe turns it into gloomand makes it deep darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you will not listen,  my soul will weep in secret for your
        pride;my eyes will weep bitterly and run down with tears,because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        flock has been taken captive.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Say to the king and the queen mother:\u201CTake a lowly seat,for
        your beautiful crownhas come down from your head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The cities of the Negeb are shut up,with none to open them;all
        Judah is taken into exile,wholly taken into exile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CLift up your eyes and seethose who come from the north.Where
        is the flock that was given you,your beautiful flock?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'What will you say when they set as head over youthose whom you yourself
        have taught to be friends to you?  Will not pangs take hold of youlike those
        of a woman in labor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And if you say in your heart,  \u2018Why have these things come upon
        me?\u2019it is for the greatness of your iniquitythat your skirts are lifted
        upand you suffer violence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Can the Ethiopian change his skinor the leopard his spots?Then
        also you can do goodwho are accustomed to do evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I will scatter you[[COMMENT(0)]]  like chaffdriven by the wind from
        the desert.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:24 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  This is your lot,the portion I have measured out to you, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,because you have forgotten meand trusted
        in lies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  I myself will lift up your skirts over your face,and your shame
        will be seen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "I have seen your abominations,your adulteries and neighings, your
        lewd whorings,  on the hills in the field.Woe to you, O Jerusalem!How long
        will it be before you are made clean?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Famine, Sword, and Pestilence'
      title: Famine, Sword, and Pestilence
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that came to Jeremiah
        concerning the drought:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "  \u201CJudah mourns,and her gates languish;her people lament on
        the ground,and the cry of Jerusalem goes up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Her nobles send their servants for water;they come to the cisterns;they
        find no water;they return with their vessels empty;they are ashamed and confoundedand
        cover their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because of the ground that is dismayed,since there is no rain on
        the land,the farmers are ashamed;they cover their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Even the doe in the field forsakes her newborn fawnbecause there
        is no grass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The wild donkeys stand on the bare heights;they pant for air like
        jackals;their eyes failbecause there is no vegetation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThough our iniquities testify against us,act, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for your name\u2019s sake;  for our backslidings are many;  we have sinned
        against you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  O you hope of Israel,its savior in time of trouble,why should you
        be like a stranger in the land,like a traveler who turns aside to tarry for
        a night?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Why should you be like a man confused,  like a mighty warrior who
        cannot save?Yet you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, are in the midst of us,and
        we are called by your name;  do not leave us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning this people:\u201CThey
        have loved to wander thus;they have not restrained their feet;  therefore
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does not accept them;  now he will remember
        their iniquityand punish their sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CDo not pray for
        the welfare of this people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Lying Prophets'
      title: Lying Prophets
      number: 12
      content: "Though they fast, I will not hear their cry, and though they offer
        burnt offering and grain offering, I will not accept them. But I will consume
        them by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then I said: \u201CAh, Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, behold, the
        prophets say to them, \u2018You shall not see the sword, nor shall you have
        famine, but I will give you assured peace in this place.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CThe prophets
        are prophesying lies in my name. I did not send them, nor did I command them
        or speak to them. They are prophesying to you a lying vision, worthless divination,
        and the deceit of their own minds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning the
        prophets who prophesy in my name although I did not send them, and who say,
        \u2018Sword and famine shall not come upon this land\u2019: By sword and
        famine those prophets shall be consumed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the people to whom they prophesy shall be cast out in the streets
        of Jerusalem, victims of famine and sword, with none to bury them\u2014them,
        their wives, their sons, and their daughters. For I will pour out their evil
        upon them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou shall say to them this word:  \u2018Let my eyes run down
        with tears night and day,and let them not cease,for the virgin daughter of
        my people is shattered with a great wound,  with a very grievous blow.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  If I go out into the field,behold, those pierced by the sword! 
        And if I enter the city,behold, the diseases of famine!  For both prophet
        and priest ply their trade through the landand have no knowledge.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Have you utterly rejected Judah?Does your soul loathe Zion?Why
        have you struck us down  so that there is no healing for us?  We looked for
        peace, but no good came;  for a time of healing, but behold, terror.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  We acknowledge our wickedness, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        the iniquity of our fathers,  for we have sinned against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Do not spurn us, for your name\u2019s sake;do not dishonor your glorious
        throne;  remember and do not break your covenant with us.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Are there any among the false gods of the nations that can bring rain?Or
        can the heavens give showers?Are you not he, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God?We set our hope on you,  for you do all these things.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Will Not Relent'
      title: The  Will Not Relent
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to me, \u201CThough Moses and Samuel stood before me, yet my heart would
        not turn toward this people. Send them out of my sight, and let them go! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when they ask you, \u2018Where shall we go?\u2019 you shall say
        to them, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201C\u2018Those
        who are for pestilence, to pestilence,and those who are for the sword, to
        the sword;those who are for famine, to famine,and those who are for captivity,
        to captivity.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  I will appoint over them four kinds of destroyers, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: the sword to kill, the dogs to tear, and the
        birds of the air and the beasts of the earth to devour and destroy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will make them a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth because
        of what Manasseh the son of Hezekiah, king of Judah, did in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CWho will have pity on you, O Jerusalem,  or who will grieve
        for you?Who will turn asideto ask about your welfare?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  You have rejected me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        you keep going backward,so I have stretched out my hand against you and destroyed
        you\u2014  I am weary of relenting.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  I have winnowed them with a winnowing forkin the gates of the land;I
        have bereaved them; I have destroyed my people;  they did not turn from their
        ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I have made their widows more in numberthan the sand of the seas;I
        have brought against the mothers of young mena destroyer at noonday;I have
        made anguish and terrorfall upon them suddenly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      number: 9
      content: "  She who bore seven has grown feeble;  she has fainted away;  her
        sun went down while it was yet day;she has been shamed and disgraced.And
        the rest of them I will give to the swordbefore their enemies,declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Woe is me, my mother, that you bore me, a man of strife and contention
        to the whole land! I have not lent, nor have I borrowed, yet all of them
        curse me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CHave I not[[COMMENT(0)]]
        set you free for their good? Have I not pleaded for you before the enemy
        in the time of trouble and in the time of distress? "
      comments:
      - number: '15:11 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Can one break iron, iron from the north, and bronze?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CYour wealth and your treasures I will give as spoil, without
        price, for all your sins, throughout all your territory. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will make you serve your enemies in a land that you do not know,
        for in my anger a fire is kindled that shall burn forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you know;  remember me and visit
        me,    and take vengeance for me on my persecutors.In your forbearance take
        me not away;  know that for your sake I bear reproach.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Your words were found, and I ate them,and your words became to me
        a joyand the delight of my heart,  for I am called by your name,O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        God of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  I did not sit in the company of revelers,nor did I rejoice;  I
        sat alone, because your hand was upon me,for you had filled me with indignation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Why is my pain unceasing,  my wound incurable,refusing to be healed?Will
        you be to me like a deceitful brook,like waters that fail?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CIf you
        return, I will restore you,and you shall stand before me.If you utter what
        is precious, and not what is worthless,you shall be as my mouth.They shall
        turn to you,but you shall not turn to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  And I will make you to this peoplea fortified wall of bronze;they
        will fight against you,  but they shall not prevail over you,  for I am with
        youto save you and deliver you,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  I will deliver you out of the hand of the wicked,and redeem you
        from the grasp of the ruthless.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Famine, Sword, and Death'
      title: Famine, Sword, and Death
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CYou shall not take a wife, nor shall you have sons or daughters
        in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning the sons
        and daughters who are born in this place, and concerning the mothers who
        bore them and the fathers who fathered them in this land: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They shall die of deadly diseases. They shall not be lamented, nor
        shall they be buried. They shall be as dung on the surface of the ground.
        They shall perish by the sword and by famine, and their dead bodies shall
        be food for the birds of the air and for the beasts of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Do not enter
        the house of mourning, or go to lament or grieve for them, for I have taken
        away my peace from this people, my steadfast love and mercy, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Both great and small shall die in this land. They shall not be buried,
        and no one shall lament for them or cut himself or make himself bald for
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'No one shall break bread for the mourner, to comfort him for the
        dead, nor shall anyone give him the cup of consolation to drink for his father
        or his mother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You shall not go into the house of feasting to sit with them, to
        eat and drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of
        Israel: Behold, I will silence in this place, before your eyes and in your
        days, the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom
        and the voice of the bride.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAnd when you tell this people all these words, and they say
        to you, \u2018Why has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> pronounced all this
        great evil against us? What is our iniquity? What is the sin that we have
        committed against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "then you shall say to them: \u2018Because your fathers have forsaken
        me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and have gone after other gods
        and have served and worshiped them, and have forsaken me and have not kept
        my law, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and because you have done worse than your fathers, for behold, every
        one of you follows his stubborn, evil will, refusing to listen to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The  Will Restore Israel'
      title: The  Will Restore Israel
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore I will hurl you out of this land into a land that neither
        you nor your fathers have known, and there you shall serve other gods day
        and night, for I will show you no favor.\u2019<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  \u201CTherefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when it shall no longer be said, \u2018As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives who brought up the people of Israel out of the land of Egypt,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but \u2018As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives who brought up
        the people of Israel out of the north country and out of all the countries
        where he had driven them.\u2019 For I will bring them back to their own land
        that I gave to their fathers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am sending for many fishers, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and they shall catch them. And afterward I will send for many hunters, and
        they shall hunt them from every mountain and every hill, and out of the clefts
        of the rocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For my eyes are on all their ways. They are not hidden from me, nor
        is their iniquity concealed from my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But first I will doubly repay their iniquity and their sin, because
        they have polluted my land with the carcasses of their detestable idols,
        and have filled my inheritance with their abominations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, my strength and my stronghold, 
        my refuge in the day of trouble,  to you shall the nations comefrom the ends
        of the earth and say:\u201COur fathers have inherited nothing but lies, 
        worthless things in which there is no profit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Can man make for himself gods?Such are not gods!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, I will make them know, this once I will
        make them know my power and my might, and they shall know that my name is
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sin of Judah'
      title: The Sin of Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThe sin of Judah is written with a pen of iron; with a point
        of diamond it is engraved on the tablet of their heart, and on the horns
        of their altars, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'while their children remember their altars and their Asherim, beside
        every green tree and on the high hills, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'on the mountains in the open country. Your wealth and all your treasures
        I will give for spoil as the price of your high places for sin throughout
        all your territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall loosen your hand from your heritage that I gave to you,
        and I will make you serve your enemies in a land that you do not know, for
        in my anger a fire is kindled that shall burn forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CCursed is the man
        who trusts in manand makes flesh his strength,[[COMMENT(0)]]whose heart turns
        away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  He is like a shrub in the desert,  and shall not see any good come.He
        shall dwell in the parched places of the wilderness,in an uninhabited salt
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CBlessed is the man who trusts in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        whose trust is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  He is like a tree planted by water,that sends out its roots by
        the stream,and does not fear when heat comes,for its leaves remain green,and
        is not anxious in the year of drought,for it does not cease to bear fruit.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The heart is deceitful above all things,and desperately sick;who
        can understand it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CI the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> search the heart  and test
        the mind,[[COMMENT(0)]]  to give every man according to his ways,according
        to the fruit of his deeds.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Like the partridge that gathers a brood that she did not hatch,so
        is he who gets riches but not by justice;  in the midst of his days they
        will leave him,  and at his end he will be a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A glorious throne set on high from the beginningis the place of our
        sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jeremiah Prays for Deliverance'
      title: Jeremiah Prays for Deliverance
      number: 13
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the hope of Israel,  all who forsake
        you shall be put to shame;those who turn away from you[[COMMENT(0)]]  shall
        be written in the earth,for they have forsaken the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the fountain of living water.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Heal me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and I shall be healed;save
        me, and I shall be saved,for you are my praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  Behold, they say to me,\u201CWhere is the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Let
        it come!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I have not run away from being your shepherd,nor have I desired the
        day of sickness.  You know what came out of my lips;it was before your face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Be not a terror to me;  you are my refuge in the day of disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Keep the Sabbath Holy'
      title: Keep the Sabbath Holy
      number: 18
      content: '  Let those be put to shame who persecute me,but let me not be put
        to shame;  let them be dismayed,but let me not be dismayed;  bring upon them
        the day of disaster;destroy them with double destruction!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Thus said the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to me: \u201CGo and stand
        in the People\u2019s Gate, by which the kings of Judah enter and by which
        they go out, and in all the gates of Jerusalem, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and say: \u2018Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you kings of Judah, and all Judah, and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem,
        who enter by these gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Take care for the sake
        of your lives, and do not bear a burden on the Sabbath day or bring it in
        by the gates of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And do not carry a burden out of your houses on the Sabbath or do
        any work, but keep the Sabbath day holy, as I commanded your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Yet they did not listen or incline their ear, but stiffened their
        neck, that they might not hear and receive instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201C\u2018But if you listen to me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and bring in no burden by the gates of this city on the Sabbath day, but
        keep the Sabbath day holy and do no work on it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then there shall enter by the gates of this city kings and princes
        who sit on the throne of David, riding in chariots and on horses, they and
        their officials, the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. And this
        city shall be inhabited forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And people shall come from the cities of Judah and the places around
        Jerusalem, from the land of Benjamin, from the Shephelah, from the hill country,
        and from the Negeb, bringing burnt offerings and sacrifices, grain offerings
        and frankincense, and bringing thank offerings to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But if you do not listen to me, to keep the Sabbath day holy, and
        not to bear a burden and enter by the gates of Jerusalem on the Sabbath day,
        then I will kindle a fire in its gates, and it shall devour the palaces of
        Jerusalem and shall not be quenched.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Potter and the Clay'
      title: The Potter and the Clay
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CArise, and go down to the potter\u2019s house, and there I
        will let you hear[[COMMENT(0)]] my words.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '18:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I went down to the potter\u2019s house, and there he was working
        at his wheel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the vessel he was making of clay was spoiled in the potter\u2019s
        hand, and he reworked it into another vessel, as it seemed good to the potter
        to do.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CO house of Israel, can I not do with you as this potter has
        done? declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Behold, like the clay in
        the potter\u2019s hand, so are you in my hand, O house of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If at any time I declare concerning a nation or a kingdom, that I
        will pluck up and break down and destroy it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and if that nation, concerning which I have spoken, turns from its
        evil, I will relent of the disaster that I intended to do to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And if at any time I declare concerning a nation or a kingdom that
        I will build and plant it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and if it does evil in my sight, not listening to my voice, then
        I will relent of the good that I had intended to do to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now, therefore, say to the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem:
        \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Behold, I am shaping disaster
        against you and devising a plan against you. Return, every one from his evil
        way, and amend your ways and your deeds.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CBut they say, \u2018That is in vain! We will follow our own
        plans, and will every one act according to the stubbornness of his evil heart.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  Ask among
        the nations,Who has heard the like of this?The virgin Israelhas done a very
        horrible thing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Does the snow of Lebanon leavethe crags of Sirion?[[COMMENT(0)]]Do
        the mountain waters run dry,the cold flowing streams?  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  But my people have forgotten me;they make offerings to false gods;they
        made them stumble in their ways,  in the ancient roads,and to walk into side
        roads,  not the highway,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'making their land a horror,a thing to be hissed at forever.  Everyone
        who passes by it is horrified  and shakes his head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  Like the east wind I will scatter thembefore the enemy.  I will
        show them my back, not my face,in the day of their calamity.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they said, \u201CCome, let us make plots against Jeremiah, for
        the law shall not perish from the priest, nor counsel from the wise, nor
        the word from the prophet. Come, let us strike him with the tongue, and let
        us not pay attention to any of his words.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hear me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and listen to the voice of
        my adversaries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Should good be repaid with evil?Yet they have dug a pit for my
        life.  Remember how I stood before youto speak good for them,to turn away
        your wrath from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore deliver up their children to famine;give them over to the
        power of the sword;let their wives become childless and widowed.May their
        men meet death by pestilence,their youths be struck down by the sword in
        battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  May a cry be heard from their houses,when you bring the plunderer
        suddenly upon them!For they have dug a pit to take me  and laid snares for
        my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Yet you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, knowall their plotting to
        kill me.  Forgive not their iniquity,nor blot out their sin from your sight.Let
        them be overthrown before you;deal with them in the time of your anger.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Broken Flask'
      title: The Broken Flask
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CGo, buy a potter\u2019s
        earthenware flask, and take some of the elders of the people and some of
        the elders of the priests, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and go out to the Valley of the Son of Hinnom at the entry of the
        Potsherd Gate, and proclaim there the words that I tell you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You shall say, \u2018Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        O kings of Judah and inhabitants of Jerusalem. Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, I am bringing such disaster upon this
        place that the ears of everyone who hears of it will tingle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because the people have forsaken me and have profaned this place
        by making offerings in it to other gods whom neither they nor their fathers
        nor the kings of Judah have known; and because they have filled this place
        with the blood of innocents, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and have built the high places of Baal to burn their sons in the
        fire as burnt offerings to Baal, which I did not command or decree, nor did
        it come into my mind\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'therefore, behold, days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when this place shall no more be called Topheth, or the Valley of the Son
        of Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And in this place I will make void the plans of Judah and Jerusalem,
        and will cause their people to fall by the sword before their enemies, and
        by the hand of those who seek their life. I will give their dead bodies for
        food to the birds of the air and to the beasts of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I will make this city a horror, a thing to be hissed at. Everyone
        who passes by it will be horrified and will hiss because of all its wounds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I will make them eat the flesh of their sons and their daughters,
        and everyone shall eat the flesh of his neighbor in the siege and in the
        distress, with which their enemies and those who seek their life afflict
        them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThen you shall break the flask in the sight of the men who
        go with you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts: So will I break this people and this city, as one breaks a potter\u2019s
        vessel, so that it can never be mended. Men shall bury in Topheth because
        there will be no place else to bury. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus will I do to this place, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and to its inhabitants, making this city like Topheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The houses of Jerusalem and the houses of the kings of Judah\u2014all
        the houses on whose roofs offerings have been offered to all the host of
        heaven, and drink offerings have been poured out to other gods\u2014shall
        be defiled like the place of Topheth.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Jeremiah came from Topheth, where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had sent him to prophesy, and he stood in the court of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        house and said to all the people: "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel, behold, I am bringing upon this city and upon all its towns all
        the disaster that I have pronounced against it, because they have stiffened
        their neck, refusing to hear my words.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Persecuted by Pashhur'
      title: Jeremiah Persecuted by Pashhur
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Pashhur the priest, the son of Immer, who was chief officer
        in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, heard Jeremiah prophesying
        these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Pashhur beat Jeremiah the prophet, and put him in the stocks
        that were in the upper Benjamin Gate of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The next day, when Pashhur released Jeremiah from the stocks, Jeremiah
        said to him, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does not call your name
        Pashhur, but Terror on Every Side. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Behold, I will make
        you a terror to yourself and to all your friends. They shall fall by the
        sword of their enemies while you look on. And I will give all Judah into
        the hand of the king of Babylon. He shall carry them captive to Babylon,
        and shall strike them down with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Moreover, I will give all the wealth of the city, all its gains,
        all its prized belongings, and all the treasures of the kings of Judah into
        the hand of their enemies, who shall plunder them and seize them and carry
        them to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And you, Pashhur, and all who dwell in your house, shall go into
        captivity. To Babylon you shall go, and there you shall die, and there you
        shall be buried, you and all your friends, to whom you have prophesied falsely.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you have deceived me,and I was deceived; 
        you are stronger than I,and you have prevailed.  I have become a laughingstock
        all the day;everyone mocks me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For whenever I speak, I cry out,I shout, \u201CViolence and destruction!\u201DFor
        the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has become for me  a reproach
        and derision all day long.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If I say, \u201CI will not mention him,or speak any more in his name,\u201D 
        there is in my heart as it were a burning fireshut up in my bones,and I am
        weary with holding it in,and I cannot.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  For I hear many whispering.  Terror is on every side!\u201CDenounce
        him! Let us denounce him!\u201Dsay all my close friends,  watching for my
        fall.\u201CPerhaps he will be deceived;then we can overcome himand take our
        revenge on him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is with me as a dread warrior;therefore
        my persecutors will stumble;  they will not overcome me.  They will be greatly
        shamed,for they will not succeed.Their eternal dishonorwill never be forgotten.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, who tests the righteous, 
        who sees the heart and the mind,[[COMMENT(0)]]let me see your vengeance upon
        them,for to you have I committed my cause.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!For
        he has delivered the life of the needyfrom the hand of evildoers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Cursed be the dayon which I was born!The day when my mother bore
        me,let it not be blessed!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Cursed be the man who brought the news to my father,\u201CA son is
        born to you,\u201D  making him very glad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Let that man be like the citiesthat the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        overthrew without pity;  let him hear a cry in the morningand an alarm at
        noon,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  because he did not kill me in the womb;so my mother would have
        been my grave,and her womb forever great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Why did I come out from the womb  to see toil and sorrow,and spend
        my days in shame?'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem Will Fall to Nebuchadnezzar'
      title: Jerusalem Will Fall to Nebuchadnezzar
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when King Zedekiah sent to him Pashhur the son of Malchiah and Zephaniah
        the priest, the son of Maaseiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CInquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for us, for Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]]
        king of Babylon is making war against us. Perhaps the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will deal with us according to all his wonderful deeds and will make him
        withdraw from us.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:2 '
        content: "Hebrew , an alternate spelling of (king of Babylon) occurring frequently
          from Jeremiah 21\u201352; this latter spelling is used throughout Jeremiah
          for consistency"
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to them: \u201CThus you shall say to Zedekiah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel:
        Behold, I will turn back the weapons of war that are in your hands and with
        which you are fighting against the king of Babylon and against the Chaldeans
        who are besieging you outside the walls. And I will bring them together into
        the midst of this city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I myself will fight against you with outstretched hand and strong
        arm, in anger and in fury and in great wrath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I will strike down the inhabitants of this city, both man and
        beast. They shall die of a great pestilence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Afterward, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I will give
        Zedekiah king of Judah and his servants and the people in this city who survive
        the pestilence, sword, and famine into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of
        Babylon and into the hand of their enemies, into the hand of those who seek
        their lives. He shall strike them down with the edge of the sword. He shall
        not pity them or spare them or have compassion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd to this people you shall say: \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        Behold, I set before you the way of life and the way of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who stays in this city shall die by the sword, by famine, and
        by pestilence, but he who goes out and surrenders to the Chaldeans who are
        besieging you shall live and shall have his life as a prize of war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Message to the House of David'
      title: Message to the House of David
      number: 10
      content: "For I have set my face against this city for harm and not for good,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: it shall be given into the hand
        of the king of Babylon, and he shall burn it with fire.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAnd to the house of the king of Judah say, \u2018Hear the word
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O house of David! Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201C\u2018Execute
        justice in the morning,and deliver from the hand of the oppressorhim who
        has been robbed,  lest my wrath go forth like fire,and burn with none to
        quench it,because of your evil deeds.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CBehold, I am against you, O inhabitant of the valley,O rock
        of the plain,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;you who say, \u2018Who
        shall come down against us,or who shall enter our habitations?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  I will punish you according to the fruit of your deeds,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;  I will kindle a fire in her forest,  and
        it shall devour all that is around her.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CGo down to the
        house of the king of Judah and speak there this word, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and say, \u2018Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        O king of Judah, who sits on the throne of David, you, and your servants,
        and your people who enter these gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Do justice and righteousness,
        and deliver from the hand of the oppressor him who has been robbed. And do
        no wrong or violence to the resident alien, the fatherless, and the widow,
        nor shed innocent blood in this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For if you will indeed obey this word, then there shall enter the
        gates of this house kings who sit on the throne of David, riding in chariots
        and on horses, they and their servants and their people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But if you will not obey these words, I swear by myself, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that this house shall become a desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning the house
        of the king of Judah:\u201C\u2018You are like Gilead to me,like the summit
        of Lebanon,yet surely I will make you a desert,  an uninhabited city.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  I will prepare destroyers against you,each with his weapons,  and
        they shall cut down your choicest cedarsand cast them into the fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201C\u2018And many nations will pass by this city, and every man
        will say to his neighbor, \u201CWhy has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> dealt
        thus with this great city?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And they will answer, \u201CBecause they have forsaken the covenant
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God and worshiped other gods and
        served them.\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Message to the Sons of Josiah'
      title: Message to the Sons of Josiah
      number: 10
      content: '  Weep not for him who is dead,nor grieve for him,  but weep bitterly
        for him who goes away,for he shall return no moreto see his native land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning Shallum
        the son of Josiah, king of Judah, who reigned instead of Josiah his father,
        and who went away from this place: \u201CHe shall return here no more, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "but in the place where they have carried him captive, there shall
        he die, and he shall never see this land again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  \u201CWoe to him who builds his house by unrighteousness,and his
        upper rooms by injustice,  who makes his neighbor serve him for nothingand
        does not give him his wages,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "who says, \u2018I will build myself a great housewith spacious upper
        rooms,\u2019who cuts out windows for it,paneling it with cedarand painting
        it with vermilion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Do you think you are a kingbecause you compete in cedar?Did not your
        father eat and drinkand do justice and righteousness?  Then it was well with
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  He judged the cause of the poor and needy;  then it was well.Is
        not this to know me?declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But you have eyes and heartonly for your dishonest gain,  for shedding
        innocent blood,and for practicing oppression and violence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning Jehoiakim
        the son of Josiah, king of Judah:  \u201CThey shall not lament for him, saying, 
        \u2018Ah, my brother!\u2019 or \u2018Ah, sister!\u2019They shall not lament
        for him, saying,  \u2018Ah, lord!\u2019 or \u2018Ah, his majesty!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "With the burial of a donkey he shall be buried,dragged and dumped
        beyond the gates of Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CGo up to Lebanon, and cry out,and lift up your voice in Bashan;cry
        out from Abarim,for all your lovers are destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I spoke to you in your prosperity,but you said, \u2018I will not
        listen.\u2019  This has been your way from your youth,that you have not obeyed
        my voice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The wind shall shepherd all your shepherds,and your lovers shall
        go into captivity;  then you will be ashamed and confoundedbecause of all
        your evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "O inhabitant of Lebanon,nested among the cedars,how you will be pitied
        when pangs come upon you,  pain as of a woman in labor!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201CAs I live, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, though
        Coniah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, were the signet ring on my right
        hand, yet I would tear you off "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and give you into the hand of those who seek your life, into the
        hand of those of whom you are afraid, even into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon and into the hand of the Chaldeans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will hurl you and the mother who bore you into another country,
        where you were not born, and there you shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But to the land to which they will long to return, there they shall
        not return.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Is this man Coniah a despised, broken pot,a vessel no one cares for?Why
        are he and his children hurled and castinto a land that they do not know?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  O land, land, land,hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CWrite this man down
        as childless,a man who shall not succeed in his days,  for none of his offspring
        shall succeed  in sitting on the throne of Davidand ruling again in Judah.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Righteous Branch'
      title: The Righteous Branch
      number: 1
      content: "    \u201CWoe to the shepherds who destroy and scatter the sheep
        of my pasture!\u201D declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        concerning the shepherds who care for my people: \u201CYou have scattered
        my flock and have driven them away, and you have not attended to them. Behold,
        I will attend to you for your evil deeds, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I will gather the remnant of my flock out of all the countries
        where I have driven them, and I will bring them back to their fold, and they
        shall be fruitful and multiply. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will set shepherds over them who will care for them, and they shall
        fear no more, nor be dismayed, neither shall any be missing, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  \u201CBehold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when I will raise up for David a righteous Branch, and he shall reign as
        king and deal wisely, and shall execute justice and righteousness in the
        land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In his days Judah will be saved, and Israel will dwell securely.
        And this is the name by which he will be called: \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is our righteousness.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  \u201CTherefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when they shall no longer say, \u2018As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives
        who brought up the people of Israel out of the land of Egypt,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Lying Prophets'
      title: Lying Prophets
      number: 8
      content: "but \u2018As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives who brought up
        and led the offspring of the house of Israel out of the north country and
        out of all the countries where he[[COMMENT(0)]] had driven them.\u2019 Then
        they shall dwell in their own land.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:8 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Concerning the prophets:  My heart is broken within me;  all my bones
        shake;I am like a drunken man,like a man overcome by wine,because of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and because of his holy words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  For the land is full of adulterers;  because of the curse the land
        mourns,and the pastures of the wilderness are dried up.  Their course is
        evil,and their might is not right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  \u201CBoth prophet and priest are ungodly;even in my house I have
        found their evil,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  Therefore their way shall be to themlike slippery paths in the
        darkness,into which they shall be driven and fall,for I will bring disaster
        upon them  in the year of their punishment,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In the prophets of Samaria  I saw an unsavory thing:  they prophesied
        by Baal  and led my people Israel astray.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But in the prophets of JerusalemI have seen a horrible thing:  they
        commit adultery and walk in lies;  they strengthen the hands of evildoers,so
        that no one turns from his evil;  all of them have become like Sodom to me, 
        and its inhabitants like Gomorrah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts concerning
        the prophets:  \u201CBehold, I will feed them with bitter food  and give
        them poisoned water to drink,for from the prophets of Jerusalemungodliness
        has gone out into all the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: \u201CDo not
        listen to the words of the prophets who prophesy to you, filling you with
        vain hopes. They speak visions of their own minds, not from the mouth of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They say continually to those who despise the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u2018It shall be well with you\u2019; and to everyone who stubbornly follows
        his own heart, they say, \u2018No disaster shall come upon you.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For who among them has stood in the council of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>to
        see and to hear his word,or who has paid attention to his word and listened?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Behold, the storm of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Wrath has
        gone forth,  a whirling tempest;it will burst upon the head of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  The anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not turn backuntil
        he has executed and accomplishedthe intents of his heart.  In the latter
        days you will understand it clearly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CI did not send the prophets,yet they ran;I did not speak
        to them,yet they prophesied.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  But if they had stood in my council,then they would have proclaimed
        my words to my people,  and they would have turned them from their evil way,and
        from the evil of their deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  \u201CAm I a God at hand, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and not a God far away? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Can a man hide himself in secret places so that I cannot see him?
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Do I not fill heaven and earth?
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I have heard what the prophets have said who prophesy lies in my
        name, saying, \u2018I have dreamed, I have dreamed!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'How long shall there be lies in the heart of the prophets who prophesy
        lies, and who prophesy the deceit of their own heart, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'who think to make my people forget my name by their dreams that they
        tell one another, even as their fathers forgot my name for Baal? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Let the prophet who has a dream tell the dream, but let him who has
        my word speak my word faithfully. What has straw in common with wheat? declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Is not my word like fire, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and like a hammer that breaks the rock in pieces? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Therefore, behold, I am against the prophets, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who steal my words from one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Behold, I am against the prophets, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who use their tongues and declare, \u2018declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Behold, I am against those who prophesy lying dreams, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and who tell them and lead my people astray
        by their lies and their recklessness, when I did not send them or charge
        them. So they do not profit this people at all, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  \u201CWhen one of this people, or a prophet or a priest asks you,
        \u2018What is the burden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u2019 you shall
        say to them, \u2018You are the burden,[[COMMENT(0)]] and I will cast you
        off, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '23:33 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And as for the prophet, priest, or one of the people who says, \u2018The
        burden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2019 I will punish that man and
        his household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Thus shall you say, every one to his neighbor and every one to his
        brother, \u2018What has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answered?\u2019 or
        \u2018What has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But \u2018the burden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019 you
        shall mention no more, for the burden is every man\u2019s own word, and you
        pervert the words of the living God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts,
        our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus you shall say to the prophet, \u2018What has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        answered you?\u2019 or \u2018What has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoken?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But if you say, \u2018The burden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2019
        thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018Because you have said these
        words, \u201CThe burden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201D when I
        sent to you, saying, \u201CYou shall not say, \u2018The burden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'therefore, behold, I will surely lift you up[[COMMENT(0)]] and cast
        you away from my presence, you and the city that I gave to you and your fathers. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:39 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And I will bring upon you everlasting reproach and perpetual shame,
        which shall not be forgotten.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Good Figs and the Bad Figs'
      title: The Good Figs and the Bad Figs
      number: 1
      content: '    After Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had taken into exile from
        Jerusalem Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, together with the
        officials of Judah, the craftsmen, and the metal workers, and had brought
        them to Babylon, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> showed me this vision: behold,
        two baskets of figs placed before the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'One basket had very good figs, like first-ripe figs, but the other
        basket had very bad figs, so bad that they could not be eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CWhat do you
        see, Jeremiah?\u201D I said, \u201CFigs, the good figs very good, and the
        bad figs very bad, so bad that they cannot be eaten.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel:
        Like these good figs, so I will regard as good the exiles from Judah, whom
        I have sent away from this place to the land of the Chaldeans. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will set my eyes on them for good, and I will bring them back to
        this land. I will build them up, and not tear them down; I will plant them,
        and not pluck them up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will give them a heart to know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and they shall be my people and I will be their God, for they shall return
        to me with their whole heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Like the bad
        figs that are so bad they cannot be eaten, so will I treat Zedekiah the king
        of Judah, his officials, the remnant of Jerusalem who remain in this land,
        and those who dwell in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will make them a horror[[COMMENT(0)]] to all the kingdoms of the
        earth, to be a reproach, a byword, a taunt, and a curse in all the places
        where I shall drive them. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:9 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I will send sword, famine, and pestilence upon them, until they
        shall be utterly destroyed from the land that I gave to them and their fathers.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Seventy Years of Captivity'
      title: Seventy Years of Captivity
      number: 1
      content: '    The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the people of Judah,
        in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah (that was
        the first year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'which Jeremiah the prophet spoke to all the people of Judah and all
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CFor twenty-three years, from the thirteenth year of Josiah
        the son of Amon, king of Judah, to this day, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has come to me, and I have spoken persistently to you, but you have not listened. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You have neither listened nor inclined your ears to hear, although
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  persistently sent to you all his servants
        the prophets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "saying, \u2018Turn now, every one of you, from his evil way and evil
        deeds, and dwell upon the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given
        to you and your fathers from of old and forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Do not go after other gods to serve and worship them, or provoke
        me to anger with the work of your hands. Then I will do you no harm.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet you have not listened to me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that you might provoke me to anger with the work of your hands to your own
        harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:
        Because you have not obeyed my words, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'behold, I will send for all the tribes of the north, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and for Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon,
        my servant, and I will bring them against this land and its inhabitants,
        and against all these surrounding nations. I will devote them to destruction,
        and make them a horror, a hissing, and an everlasting desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Moreover, I will banish from them the voice of mirth and the voice
        of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride, the
        grinding of the millstones and the light of the lamp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This whole land shall become a ruin and a waste, and these nations
        shall serve the king of Babylon seventy years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then after seventy years are completed, I will punish the king of
        Babylon and that nation, the land of the Chaldeans, for their iniquity, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, making the land an everlasting waste. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will bring upon that land all the words that I have uttered against
        it, everything written in this book, which Jeremiah prophesied against all
        the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: The Cup of the \u2019s Wrath"
      title: "The Cup of the \u2019s Wrath"
      number: 14
      content: "For many nations and great kings shall make slaves even of them,
        and I will recompense them according to their deeds and the work of their
        hands.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Thus the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, said to
        me: \u201CTake from my hand this cup of the wine of wrath, and make all the
        nations to whom I send you drink it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "They shall drink and stagger and be crazed because of the sword that
        I am sending among them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So I took the cup from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s hand,
        and made all the nations to whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent me
        drink it: "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Jerusalem and the cities of Judah, its kings and officials, to make
        them a desolation and a waste, a hissing and a curse, as at this day; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pharaoh king of Egypt, his servants, his officials, all his people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and all the mixed tribes among them; all the kings of the land of
        Uz and all the kings of the land of the Philistines (Ashkelon, Gaza, Ekron,
        and the remnant of Ashdod); '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Edom, Moab, and the sons of Ammon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'all the kings of Tyre, all the kings of Sidon, and the kings of the
        coastland across the sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Dedan, Tema, Buz, and all who cut the corners of their hair; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'all the kings of Arabia and all the kings of the mixed tribes who
        dwell in the desert; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'all the kings of Zimri, all the kings of Elam, and all the kings
        of Media; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'all the kings of the north, far and near, one after another, and
        all the kingdoms of the world that are on the face of the earth. And after
        them the king of Babylon[[COMMENT(0)]] shall drink.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:26 '
        content: Hebrew , a code name for Babylon
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CThen you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, the God of Israel: Drink, be drunk and vomit, fall and rise no
        more, because of the sword that I am sending among you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CAnd if they refuse to accept the cup from your hand to drink,
        then you shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts: You must drink! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For behold, I begin to work disaster at the city that is called by
        my name, and shall you go unpunished? You shall not go unpunished, for I
        am summoning a sword against all the inhabitants of the earth, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CYou, therefore, shall prophesy against them all these words,
        and say to them:  \u201C\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will roar from
        on high,and from his holy habitation utter his voice;he will roar mightily
        against his fold,  and shout, like those who tread grapes,against all the
        inhabitants of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The clamor will resound to the ends of the earth,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has an indictment against the nations;  he is entering into judgment with
        all flesh,and the wicked he will put to the sword,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:Behold,
        disaster is going forthfrom nation to nation,  and a great tempest is stirring 
        from the farthest parts of the earth!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  \u201CAnd those pierced by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on that
        day shall extend from one end of the earth to the other. They shall not be
        lamented, or gathered, or buried; they shall be dung on the surface of the
        ground.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "  \u201CWail, you shepherds, and cry out,  and roll in ashes, you
        lords of the flock,for the days of your slaughter and dispersion have come,and
        you shall fall like a choice vessel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'No refuge will remain for the shepherds,nor escape for the lords
        of the flock.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "A voice\u2014the cry of the shepherds,  and the wail of the lords
        of the flock!For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is laying waste their pasture,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '  and the peaceful folds are devastated  because of the fierce anger
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Like a lion he has left his lair,for their land has become a wastebecause
        of the sword of the oppressor,  and because of his fierce anger.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Threatened with Death'
      title: Jeremiah Threatened with Death
      number: 1
      content: '    In the beginning of the reign of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah,
        king of Judah, this word came from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Stand in the court
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s house, and speak to all the cities
        of Judah that come to worship in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        all the words that I command you to speak to them; do not hold back a word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It may be they will listen, and every one turn from his evil way,
        that I may relent of the disaster that I intend to do to them because of
        their evil deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall say to them, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        If you will not listen to me, to walk in my law that I have set before you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and to listen to the words of my servants the prophets whom I send
        to you urgently, though you have not listened, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "then I will make this house like Shiloh, and I will make this city
        a curse for all the nations of the earth.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The priests and the prophets and all the people heard Jeremiah
        speaking these words in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And when Jeremiah had finished speaking all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded him to speak to all the people, then the priests and the prophets
        and all the people laid hold of him, saying, \u201CYou shall die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Why have you prophesied in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        saying, \u2018This house shall be like Shiloh, and this city shall be desolate,
        without inhabitant\u2019?\u201D And all the people gathered around Jeremiah
        in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When the officials of Judah heard these things, they came up from
        the king\u2019s house to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        took their seat in the entry of the New Gate of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the priests and the prophets said to the officials and to all
        the people, \u201CThis man deserves the sentence of death, because he has
        prophesied against this city, as you have heard with your own ears.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jeremiah spoke to all the officials and all the people, saying,
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent me to prophesy against this house
        and this city all the words you have heard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now therefore mend your ways and your deeds, and obey the voice of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will relent of the disaster that he has pronounced against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But as for me, behold, I am in your hands. Do with me as seems good
        and right to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jeremiah Spared from Death'
      title: Jeremiah Spared from Death
      number: 15
      content: "Only know for certain that if you put me to death, you will bring
        innocent blood upon yourselves and upon this city and its inhabitants, for
        in truth the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent me to you to speak all these
        words in your ears.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  Then the officials and all the people said to the priests and the
        prophets, \u201CThis man does not deserve the sentence of death, for he has
        spoken to us in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And certain of the elders of the land arose and spoke to all the
        assembled people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CMicah of Moresheth prophesied in the days of Hezekiah king
        of Judah, and said to all the people of Judah: \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts,  \u201C\u2018Zion shall be plowed as a field;Jerusalem shall become
        a heap of ruins,and the mountain of the house a wooded height.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Did Hezekiah king of Judah and all Judah put him to death? Did he
        not fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and entreat the favor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and did not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> relent of the disaster that he
        had pronounced against them? But we are about to bring great disaster upon
        ourselves.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'There was another man who prophesied in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        Uriah the son of Shemaiah from Kiriath-jearim. He prophesied against this
        city and against this land in words like those of Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when King Jehoiakim, with all his warriors and all the officials,
        heard his words, the king sought to put him to death. But when Uriah heard
        of it, he was afraid and fled and escaped to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then King Jehoiakim sent to Egypt certain men, Elnathan the son of
        Achbor and others with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and they took Uriah from Egypt and brought him to King Jehoiakim,
        who struck him down with the sword and dumped his dead body into the burial
        place of the common people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: But the hand of Ahikam the son of Shaphan was with Jeremiah so that
        he was not given over to the people to be put to death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Yoke of Nebuchadnezzar'
      title: The Yoke of Nebuchadnezzar
      number: 1
      content: '  In the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah[[COMMENT(0)]] the son
        of Josiah, king of Judah, this word came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CMake yourself
        straps and yoke-bars, and put them on your neck. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Send word[[COMMENT(0)]] to the king of Edom, the king of Moab, the
        king of the sons of Ammon, the king of Tyre, and the king of Sidon by the
        hand of the envoys who have come to Jerusalem to Zedekiah king of Judah. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Give them this charge for their masters: \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, the God of Israel: This is what you shall say to your masters: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIt is I who by my great power and my outstretched arm have
        made the earth, with the men and animals that are on the earth, and I give
        it to whomever it seems right to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now I have given all these lands into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar,
        the king of Babylon, my servant, and I have given him also the beasts of
        the field to serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the nations shall serve him and his son and his grandson, until
        the time of his own land comes. Then many nations and great kings shall make
        him their slave.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201C\u2018\u201CBut if any nation or kingdom will not serve this
        Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and put its neck under the yoke of the king
        of Babylon, I will punish that nation with the sword, with famine, and with
        pestilence, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, until I have consumed
        it by his hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So do not listen to your prophets, your diviners, your dreamers,
        your fortune-tellers, or your sorcerers, who are saying to you, \u2018You
        shall not serve the king of Babylon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For it is a lie that they are prophesying to you, with the result
        that you will be removed far from your land, and I will drive you out, and
        you will perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But any nation that will bring its neck under the yoke of the king
        of Babylon and serve him, I will leave on its own land, to work it and dwell
        there, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "To Zedekiah king of Judah I spoke in like manner: \u201CBring your
        necks under the yoke of the king of Babylon, and serve him and his people
        and live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Why will you and your people die by the sword, by famine, and by
        pestilence, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken concerning any
        nation that will not serve the king of Babylon? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Do not listen to the words of the prophets who are saying to you,
        \u2018You shall not serve the king of Babylon,\u2019 for it is a lie that
        they are prophesying to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I have not sent them, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, but
        they are prophesying falsely in my name, with the result that I will drive
        you out and you will perish, you and the prophets who are prophesying to
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then I spoke to the priests and to all this people, saying, \u201CThus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Do not listen to the words of your
        prophets who are prophesying to you, saying, \u2018Behold, the vessels of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s house will now shortly be brought
        back from Babylon,\u2019 for it is a lie that they are prophesying to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not listen to them; serve the king of Babylon and live. Why should
        this city become a desolation? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'If they are prophets, and if the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is with them, then let them intercede with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, that the vessels that are left in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        in the house of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem may not go to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts concerning
        the pillars, the sea, the stands, and the rest of the vessels that are left
        in this city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon did not take away, when he took
        into exile from Jerusalem to Babylon Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim, king
        of Judah, and all the nobles of Judah and Jerusalem\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel,
        concerning the vessels that are left in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        in the house of the king of Judah, and in Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "They shall be carried to Babylon and remain there until the day when
        I visit them, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Then I will bring
        them back and restore them to this place.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hananiah the False Prophet'
      title: Hananiah the False Prophet
      number: 1
      content: '  In that same year, at the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king
        of Judah, in the fifth month of the fourth year, Hananiah the son of Azzur,
        the prophet from Gibeon, spoke to me in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        in the presence of the priests and all the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel: I have broken the yoke of the king of Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Within two years I will bring back to this place all the vessels
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s house, which Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon took away from this place and carried to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will also bring back to this place Jeconiah the son of Jehoiakim,
        king of Judah, and all the exiles from Judah who went to Babylon, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for I will break the yoke of the king of
        Babylon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the prophet Jeremiah spoke to Hananiah the prophet in the presence
        of the priests and all the people who were standing in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and the prophet Jeremiah said, \u201CAmen! May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        do so; may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make the words that you have prophesied
        come true, and bring back to this place from Babylon the vessels of the house
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and all the exiles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet hear now this word that I speak in your hearing and in the hearing
        of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The prophets who preceded you and me from ancient times prophesied
        war, famine, and pestilence against many countries and great kingdoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "As for the prophet who prophesies peace, when the word of that prophet
        comes to pass, then it will be known that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has truly sent the prophet.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the prophet Hananiah took the yoke-bars from the neck of Jeremiah
        the prophet and broke them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Hananiah spoke in the presence of all the people, saying, \u201CThus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Even so will I break the yoke of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon from the neck of all the nations within two years.\u201D
        But Jeremiah the prophet went his way.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Sometime after the prophet Hananiah had broken the yoke-bars from
        off the neck of Jeremiah the prophet, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo, tell Hananiah, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        You have broken wooden bars, but you have made in their place bars of iron. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of
        Israel: I have put upon the neck of all these nations an iron yoke to serve
        Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and they shall serve him, for I have given
        to him even the beasts of the field.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Jeremiah the prophet said to the prophet Hananiah, \u201CListen,
        Hananiah, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not sent you, and you have
        made this people trust in a lie. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u2018Behold,
        I will remove you from the face of the earth. This year you shall die, because
        you have uttered rebellion against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: In that same year, in the seventh month, the prophet Hananiah died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Letter to the Exiles"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Letter to the Exiles"
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the words of the letter that Jeremiah the prophet sent
        from Jerusalem to the surviving elders of the exiles, and to the priests,
        the prophets, and all the people, whom Nebuchadnezzar had taken into exile
        from Jerusalem to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This was after King Jeconiah and the queen mother, the eunuchs, the
        officials of Judah and Jerusalem, the craftsmen, and the metal workers had
        departed from Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The letter was sent by the hand of Elasah the son of Shaphan and
        Gemariah the son of Hilkiah, whom Zedekiah king of Judah sent to Babylon
        to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon. It said: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel, to all the exiles whom I have sent into exile from Jerusalem to
        Babylon: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Build houses and live in them; plant gardens and eat their produce. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Take wives and have sons and daughters; take wives for your sons,
        and give your daughters in marriage, that they may bear sons and daughters;
        multiply there, and do not decrease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But seek the welfare of the city where I have sent you into exile,
        and pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on its behalf, for in its welfare
        you will find your welfare. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of
        Israel: Do not let your prophets and your diviners who are among you deceive
        you, and do not listen to the dreams that they dream,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'for it is a lie that they are prophesying to you in my name; I did
        not send them, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: When seventy
        years are completed for Babylon, I will visit you, and I will fulfill to
        you my promise and bring you back to this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For I know the plans I have for you, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        plans for welfare[[COMMENT(0)]] and not for evil, to give you a future and
        a hope. '
      comments:
      - number: '29:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then you will call upon me and come and pray to me, and I will hear
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You will seek me and find me, when you seek me with all your heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will be found by you, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and I will restore your fortunes and gather you from all the nations and
        all the places where I have driven you, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and I will bring you back to the place from which I sent you into exile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CBecause you have said, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has raised up prophets for us in Babylon,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning the king who
        sits on the throne of David, and concerning all the people who dwell in this
        city, your kinsmen who did not go out with you into exile: '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, behold,
        I am sending on them sword, famine, and pestilence, and I will make them
        like vile figs that are so rotten they cannot be eaten. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will pursue them with sword, famine, and pestilence, and will make
        them a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth, to be a curse, a terror,
        a hissing, and a reproach among all the nations where I have driven them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "because they did not pay attention to my words, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that I persistently sent to you by my servants the prophets, but you would
        not listen, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all you exiles
        whom I sent away from Jerusalem to Babylon: '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel, concerning Ahab the son of Kolaiah and Zedekiah the son of Maaseiah,
        who are prophesying a lie to you in my name: Behold, I will deliver them
        into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and he shall strike them
        down before your eyes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Because of them this curse shall be used by all the exiles from Judah
        in Babylon: \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make you like Zedekiah
        and Ahab, whom the king of Babylon roasted in the fire,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Shemaiah\u2019s False Prophecy"
      title: "Shemaiah\u2019s False Prophecy"
      number: 23
      content: "because they have done an outrageous thing in Israel, they have committed
        adultery with their neighbors\u2019 wives, and they have spoken in my name
        lying words that I did not command them. I am the one who knows, and I am
        witness, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'To Shemaiah of Nehelam you shall say: '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel: You have sent letters in your name to all the people who are in
        Jerusalem, and to Zephaniah the son of Maaseiah the priest, and to all the
        priests, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has made you priest instead
        of Jehoiada the priest, to have charge in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        over every madman who prophesies, to put him in the stocks and neck irons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now why have you not rebuked Jeremiah of Anathoth who is prophesying
        to you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For he has sent to us in Babylon, saying, \u201CYour exile will be
        long; build houses and live in them, and plant gardens and eat their produce.\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Zephaniah the priest read this letter in the hearing of Jeremiah
        the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CSend to all the exiles, saying, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        concerning Shemaiah of Nehelam: Because Shemaiah had prophesied to you when
        I did not send him, and has made you trust in a lie, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Behold, I will
        punish Shemaiah of Nehelam and his descendants. He shall not have anyone
        living among this people, and he shall not see the good that I will do to
        my people, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for he has spoken rebellion
        against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Restoration for Israel and Judah'
      title: Restoration for Israel and Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel:
        Write in a book all the words that I have spoken to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For behold, days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when I will restore the fortunes of my people, Israel and Judah, says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and I will bring them back to the land that
        I gave to their fathers, and they shall take possession of it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These are the words that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke concerning
        Israel and Judah:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:We have heard a cry
        of panic,of terror, and no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ask now, and see,can a man bear a child?  Why then do I see every
        manwith his hands on his stomach like a woman in labor?  Why has every face
        turned pale?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Alas! That day is so great  there is none like it;it is a time of
        distress for Jacob;yet he shall be saved out of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd it shall come to pass in that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, that I will break his yoke from off your neck, and I will burst
        your bonds, and foreigners shall no more make a servant of him.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But they shall serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God and
        David their king, whom I will raise up for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CThen fear not, O Jacob my servant, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,nor
        be dismayed, O Israel;for behold, I will save you from far away,  and your
        offspring from the land of their captivity.  Jacob shall return and have
        quiet and ease,and none shall make him afraid.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  For I am with you to save you,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        I will make a full end of all the nationsamong whom I scattered you,but of
        you I will not make a full end.  I will discipline you in just measure,and
        I will by no means leave you unpunished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  Your hurt is
        incurable,  and your wound is grievous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There is none to uphold your cause,no medicine for your wound,  no
        healing for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  All your lovers have forgotten you;they care nothing for you;for
        I have dealt you the blow of an enemy,the punishment of a merciless foe,because
        your guilt is great,  because your sins are flagrant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Why do you cry out over your hurt?  Your pain is incurable.Because
        your guilt is great,  because your sins are flagrant,I have done these things
        to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Therefore all who devour you shall be devoured,and all your foes,
        every one of them, shall go into captivity;  those who plunder you shall
        be plundered,  and all who prey on you I will make a prey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  For I will restore health to you,and your wounds I will heal,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,because they have called you an outcast: 
        \u2018It is Zion, for whom no one cares!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:Behold, I will restore
        the fortunes of the tents of Jacoband have compassion on his dwellings;the
        city shall be rebuilt on its mound,and the palace shall stand where it used
        to be.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Out of them shall come songs of thanksgiving,and the voices of
        those who celebrate.  I will multiply them, and they shall not be few;I will
        make them honored, and they shall not be small.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Their children shall be as they were of old,and their congregation
        shall be established before me,and I will punish all who oppress them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Their prince shall be one of themselves;  their ruler shall come
        out from their midst;  I will make him draw near, and he shall approach me, 
        for who would dare of himself to approach me?declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  And you shall be my people,and I will be your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Behold the storm of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Wrath has gone
        forth,a whirling tempest;it will burst upon the head of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  The fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not turn
        backuntil he has executed and accomplishedthe intentions of his mind.  In
        the latter days you will understand this.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Will Turn Mourning to Joy'
      title: The  Will Turn Mourning to Joy
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    \u201CAt that time, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        I will be the God of all the clans of Israel, and they shall be my people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CThe people who survived
        the swordfound grace in the wilderness;  when Israel sought for rest,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to him[[COMMENT(0)]] from
        far away.  I have loved you with an everlasting love;therefore I have continued
        my faithfulness to you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:3 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Again I will build you, and you shall be built,O virgin Israel! 
        Again you shall adorn yourself with tambourinesand shall go forth in the
        dance of the merrymakers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Again you shall plant vineyardson the mountains of Samaria;the
        planters shall plantand shall enjoy the fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For there shall be a day when watchmen will callin the hill country
        of Ephraim:  \u2018Arise, and let us go up to Zion,to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CSing aloud
        with gladness for Jacob,and raise shouts for the chief of the nations;proclaim,
        give praise, and say,  \u2018O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, save your people,the
        remnant of Israel.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Behold, I will bring them from the north countryand gather them from
        the farthest parts of the earth,among them the blind and the lame,the pregnant
        woman and she who is in labor, together;a great company, they shall return
        here.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  With weeping they shall come,  and with pleas for mercy I will
        lead them back,I will make them walk by brooks of water,  in a straight path
        in which they shall not stumble,for I am a father to Israel,and Ephraim is
        my firstborn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CHear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, O nations,and
        declare it in the coastlands far away;say, \u2018He who scattered Israel
        will gather him,and will keep him as a shepherd keeps his flock.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has ransomed Jacoband has redeemed
        him from hands too strong for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They shall come and sing aloud on the height of Zion,  and they shall
        be radiant over the goodness of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  over the
        grain, the wine, and the oil,and over the young of the flock and the herd; 
        their life shall be like a watered garden,  and they shall languish no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Then shall the young women rejoice in the dance,and the young men
        and the old shall be merry.  I will turn their mourning into joy;I will comfort
        them, and give them gladness for sorrow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  I will feast the soul of the priests with abundance,and my people
        shall be satisfied with my goodness,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CA voice is heard
        in Ramah,lamentation and bitter weeping.  Rachel is weeping for her children;she
        refuses to be comforted for her children,  because they are no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CKeep your voice from
        weeping,and your eyes from tears,for there is a reward for your work,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and they shall come back from the land of
        the enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  There is hope for your future,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        your children shall come back to their own country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I have heard Ephraim grieving,\u2018You have disciplined me, and
        I was disciplined,like an untrained calf;  bring me back that I may be restored,for
        you are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For after I had turned away, I relented,and after I was instructed,
        I struck my thigh;  I was ashamed, and I was confounded,because I bore the
        disgrace of my youth.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Is Ephraim my dear son?  Is he my darling child?For as often as
        I speak against him,I do remember him still.  Therefore my heart[[COMMENT(0)]]
        yearns for him;I will surely have mercy on him,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  \u201CSet up road markers for yourself;make yourself guideposts; 
        consider well the highway,  the road by which you went.Return, O virgin Israel,return
        to these your cities.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  How long will you waver,  O faithless daughter?For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has created a new thing on the earth:a woman encircles a man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel:
        \u201COnce more they shall use these words in the land of Judah and in its
        cities, when I restore their fortunes:  \u201C\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        bless you, O habitation of righteousness,  O holy hill!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  And Judah and all its cities shall dwell there together, and the
        farmers and those who wander with their flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For I will satisfy the weary soul, and every languishing soul I will
        replenish.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'At this I awoke and looked, and my sleep was pleasant to me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  \u201CBehold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when I will sow the house of Israel and the house of Judah with the seed
        of man and the seed of beast. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And it shall come to pass that as I have watched over them to pluck
        up and break down, to overthrow, destroy, and bring harm, so I will watch
        over them to build and to plant, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "In those days they shall no longer say:  \u201C\u2018The fathers
        have eaten sour grapes,and the children\u2019s teeth are set on edge.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The New Covenant'
      title: The New Covenant
      number: 30
      content: '  But everyone shall die for his own iniquity. Each man who eats
        sour grapes, his teeth shall be set on edge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  \u201CBehold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel and the house of
        Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'not like the covenant that I made with their fathers on the day when
        I took them by the hand to bring them out of the land of Egypt, my covenant
        that they broke, though I was their husband, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel
        after those days, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: I will put my
        law within them, and I will write it on their hearts. And I will be their
        God, and they shall be my people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And no longer shall each one teach his neighbor and each his brother,
        saying, \u2018Know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2019 for they shall
        all know me, from the least of them to the greatest, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        For I will forgive their iniquity, and I will remember their sin no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who gives the sun for light
        by dayand the fixed order of the moon and the stars for light by night,who
        stirs up the sea so that its waves roar\u2014  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts is his name:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "  \u201CIf this fixed order departsfrom before me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,then
        shall the offspring of Israel ceasefrom being a nation before me forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CIf the heavens above
        can be measured,and the foundations of the earth below can be explored, 
        then I will cast off all the offspring of Israelfor all that they have done,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "  \u201CBehold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when the city shall be rebuilt for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  from
        the Tower of Hananel to the Corner Gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And the measuring line shall go out farther, straight to the hill
        Gareb, and shall then turn to Goah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "The whole valley of the dead bodies and the ashes, and all the fields
        as far as the brook Kidron, to the corner of the Horse Gate toward the east,
        shall be sacred to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. It shall not be plucked
        up or overthrown anymore forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Buys a Field During the Siege'
      title: Jeremiah Buys a Field During the Siege
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        in the tenth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, which was the eighteenth year
        of Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'At that time the army of the king of Babylon was besieging Jerusalem,
        and Jeremiah the prophet was shut up in the court of the guard that was in
        the palace of the king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For Zedekiah king of Judah had imprisoned him, saying, \u201CWhy
        do you prophesy and say, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        Behold, I am giving this city into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he
        shall capture it; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Zedekiah king of Judah shall not escape out of the hand of the Chaldeans,
        but shall surely be given into the hand of the king of Babylon, and shall
        speak with him face to face and see him eye to eye. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he shall take Zedekiah to Babylon, and there he shall remain
        until I visit him, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Though you fight
        against the Chaldeans, you shall not succeed\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jeremiah said, \u201CThe word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to me: "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Behold, Hanamel the son of Shallum your uncle will come to you and
        say, \u2018Buy my field that is at Anathoth, for the right of redemption
        by purchase is yours.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Hanamel my cousin came to me in the court of the guard, in accordance
        with the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and said to me, \u2018Buy
        my field that is at Anathoth in the land of Benjamin, for the right of possession
        and redemption is yours; buy it for yourself.\u2019 Then I knew that this
        was the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd I bought the field at Anathoth from Hanamel my cousin,
        and weighed out the money to him, seventeen shekels of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I signed the deed, sealed it, got witnesses, and weighed the money
        on scales. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then I took the sealed deed of purchase, containing the terms and
        conditions and the open copy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I gave the deed of purchase to Baruch the son of Neriah son of
        Mahseiah, in the presence of Hanamel my cousin, in the presence of the witnesses
        who signed the deed of purchase, and in the presence of all the Judeans who
        were sitting in the court of the guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I charged Baruch in their presence, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel: Take these deeds, both this sealed deed of purchase and this open
        deed, and put them in an earthenware vessel, that they may last for a long
        time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jeremiah Prays for Understanding'
      title: Jeremiah Prays for Understanding
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of
        Israel: Houses and fields and vineyards shall again be bought in this land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAfter I had given the deed of purchase to Baruch the son of
        Neriah, I prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, saying: "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Ah, Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>! It is you who have made
        the heavens and the earth by your great power and by your outstretched arm!
        Nothing is too hard for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You show steadfast love to thousands, but you repay the guilt of
        fathers to their children after them, O great and mighty God, whose name
        is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'great in counsel and mighty in deed, whose eyes are open to all the
        ways of the children of man, rewarding each one according to his ways and
        according to the fruit of his deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You have shown signs and wonders in the land of Egypt, and to this
        day in Israel and among all mankind, and have made a name for yourself, as
        at this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You brought your people Israel out of the land of Egypt with signs
        and wonders, with a strong hand and outstretched arm, and with great terror. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And you gave them this land, which you swore to their fathers to
        give them, a land flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they entered and took possession of it. But they did not obey
        your voice or walk in your law. They did nothing of all you commanded them
        to do. Therefore you have made all this disaster come upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Behold, the siege mounds have come up to the city to take it, and
        because of sword and famine and pestilence the city is given into the hands
        of the Chaldeans who are fighting against it. What you spoke has come to
        pass, and behold, you see it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Yet you, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, have said to me, \u201CBuy
        the field for money and get witnesses\u201D\u2014though the city is given
        into the hands of the Chaldeans.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of all
        flesh. Is anything too hard for me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore, thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Behold, I am
        giving this city into the hands of the Chaldeans and into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, and he shall capture it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The Chaldeans who are fighting against this city shall come and set
        this city on fire and burn it, with the houses on whose roofs offerings have
        been made to Baal and drink offerings have been poured out to other gods,
        to provoke me to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For the children of Israel and the children of Judah have done nothing
        but evil in my sight from their youth. The children of Israel have done nothing
        but provoke me to anger by the work of their hands, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'This city has aroused my anger and wrath, from the day it was built
        to this day, so that I will remove it from my sight '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "because of all the evil of the children of Israel and the children
        of Judah that they did to provoke me to anger\u2014their kings and their
        officials, their priests and their prophets, the men of Judah and the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They have turned to me their back and not their face. And though
        I have taught them persistently, they have not listened to receive instruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'They set up their abominations in the house that is called by my
        name, to defile it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: They Shall Be My People; I Will Be Their God'
      title: They Shall Be My People; I Will Be Their God
      number: 35
      content: 'They built the high places of Baal in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom,
        to offer up their sons and daughters to Molech, though I did not command
        them, nor did it enter into my mind, that they should do this abomination,
        to cause Judah to sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CNow therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of Israel, concerning this city of which you say, \u2018It is given into
        the hand of the king of Babylon by sword, by famine, and by pestilence\u2019: "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Behold, I will gather them from all the countries to which I drove
        them in my anger and my wrath and in great indignation. I will bring them
        back to this place, and I will make them dwell in safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And they shall be my people, and I will be their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'I will give them one heart and one way, that they may fear me forever,
        for their own good and the good of their children after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'I will make with them an everlasting covenant, that I will not turn
        away from doing good to them. And I will put the fear of me in their hearts,
        that they may not turn from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'I will rejoice in doing them good, and I will plant them in this
        land in faithfulness, with all my heart and all my soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Just as I have
        brought all this great disaster upon this people, so I will bring upon them
        all the good that I promise them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Fields shall be bought in this land of which you are saying, \u2018It
        is a desolation, without man or beast; it is given into the hand of the Chaldeans.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Fields shall be bought for money, and deeds shall be signed and sealed
        and witnessed, in the land of Benjamin, in the places about Jerusalem, and
        in the cities of Judah, in the cities of the hill country, in the cities
        of the Shephelah, and in the cities of the Negeb; for I will restore their
        fortunes, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Promises Peace'
      title: The  Promises Peace
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to Jeremiah a second time, while he was still shut up in the court of
        the guard: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who made the earth,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who formed it to establish it\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is his name: "
      comments:
      - number: '33:2 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Call to me and I will answer you, and will tell you great and hidden
        things that you have not known. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        concerning the houses of this city and the houses of the kings of Judah that
        were torn down to make a defense against the siege mounds and against the
        sword: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They are coming in to fight against the Chaldeans and to fill them[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with the dead bodies of men whom I shall strike down in my anger and my wrath,
        for I have hidden my face from this city because of all their evil. '
      comments:
      - number: '33:5 '
        content: That is, the torn-down houses
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Behold, I will bring to it health and healing, and I will heal them
        and reveal to them abundance of prosperity and security. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will restore the fortunes of Judah and the fortunes of Israel,
        and rebuild them as they were at first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will cleanse them from all the guilt of their sin against me, and
        I will forgive all the guilt of their sin and rebellion against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And this city[[COMMENT(0)]] shall be to me a name of joy, a praise
        and a glory before all the nations of the earth who shall hear of all the
        good that I do for them. They shall fear and tremble because of all the good
        and all the prosperity I provide for it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: In this place of
        which you say, \u2018It is a waste without man or beast,\u2019 in the cities
        of Judah and the streets of Jerusalem that are desolate, without man or inhabitant
        or beast, there shall be heard again "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "the voice of mirth and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom
        and the voice of the bride, the voices of those who sing, as they bring thank
        offerings to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201C\u2018Give
        thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is good,for his steadfast love endures forever!\u2019  For I will restore
        the fortunes of the land as at first, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: In this
        place that is waste, without man or beast, and in all of its cities, there
        shall again be habitations of shepherds resting their flocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: The \u2019s Eternal Covenant with David"
      title: "The \u2019s Eternal Covenant with David"
      number: 13
      content: 'In the cities of the hill country, in the cities of the Shephelah,
        and in the cities of the Negeb, in the land of Benjamin, the places about
        Jerusalem, and in the cities of Judah, flocks shall again pass under the
        hands of the one who counts them, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  \u201CBehold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when I will fulfill the promise I made to the house of Israel and the house
        of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days and at that time I will cause a righteous Branch to
        spring up for David, and he shall execute justice and righteousness in the
        land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "In those days Judah will be saved, and Jerusalem will dwell securely.
        And this is the name by which it will be called: \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is our righteousness.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: David shall
        never lack a man to sit on the throne of the house of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and the Levitical priests shall never lack a man in my presence to
        offer burnt offerings, to burn grain offerings, and to make sacrifices forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: If you can break
        my covenant with the day and my covenant with the night, so that day and
        night will not come at their appointed time, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'then also my covenant with David my servant may be broken, so that
        he shall not have a son to reign on his throne, and my covenant with the
        Levitical priests my ministers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As the host of heaven cannot be numbered and the sands of the sea
        cannot be measured, so I will multiply the offspring of David my servant,
        and the Levitical priests who minister to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CHave you not observed that these people are saying, \u2018The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected the two clans that he chose\u2019?
        Thus they have despised my people so that they are no longer a nation in
        their sight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: If I have not established
        my covenant with day and night and the fixed order of heaven and earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then I will reject the offspring of Jacob and David my servant and
        will not choose one of his offspring to rule over the offspring of Abraham,
        Isaac, and Jacob. For I will restore their fortunes and will have mercy on
        them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zedekiah to Die in Babylon'
      title: Zedekiah to Die in Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and all his army and all the kingdoms
        of the earth under his dominion and all the peoples were fighting against
        Jerusalem and all of its cities: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel:
        Go and speak to Zedekiah king of Judah and say to him, \u2018Thus says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: Behold, I am giving this city into the hand
        of the king of Babylon, and he shall burn it with fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You shall not escape from his hand but shall surely be captured and
        delivered into his hand. You shall see the king of Babylon eye to eye and
        speak with him face to face. And you shall go to Babylon.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, O Zedekiah
        king of Judah! Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning you:
        \u2018You shall not die by the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "You shall die in peace. And as spices were burned for your fathers,
        the former kings who were before you, so people shall burn spices for you
        and lament for you, saying, \u201CAlas, lord!\u201D\u2019 For I have spoken
        the word, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Jeremiah the prophet spoke all these words to Zedekiah king
        of Judah, in Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'when the army of the king of Babylon was fighting against Jerusalem
        and against all the cities of Judah that were left, Lachish and Azekah, for
        these were the only fortified cities of Judah that remained.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        after King Zedekiah had made a covenant with all the people in Jerusalem
        to make a proclamation of liberty to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'that everyone should set free his Hebrew slaves, male and female,
        so that no one should enslave a Jew, his brother. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they obeyed, all the officials and all the people who had entered
        into the covenant that everyone would set free his slave, male or female,
        so that they would not be enslaved again. They obeyed and set them free. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But afterward they turned around and took back the male and female
        slaves they had set free, and brought them into subjection as slaves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel:
        I myself made a covenant with your fathers when I brought them out of the
        land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018At the end of seven years each of you must set free the fellow
        Hebrew who has been sold to you and has served you six years; you must set
        him free from your service.\u2019 But your fathers did not listen to me or
        incline their ears to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You recently repented and did what was right in my eyes by proclaiming
        liberty, each to his neighbor, and you made a covenant before me in the house
        that is called by my name, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'but then you turned around and profaned my name when each of you
        took back his male and female slaves, whom you had set free according to
        their desire, and you brought them into subjection to be your slaves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore, thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: You have
        not obeyed me by proclaiming liberty, every one to his brother and to his
        neighbor; behold, I proclaim to you liberty to the sword, to pestilence,
        and to famine, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. I will make you
        a horror to all the kingdoms of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the men who transgressed my covenant and did not keep the terms
        of the covenant that they made before me, I will make them like[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        the calf that they cut in two and passed between its parts\u2014 "
      comments:
      - number: '34:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the officials of Judah, the officials of Jerusalem, the eunuchs,
        the priests, and all the people of the land who passed between the parts
        of the calf. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And I will give them into the hand of their enemies and into the
        hand of those who seek their lives. Their dead bodies shall be food for the
        birds of the air and the beasts of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Zedekiah king of Judah and his officials I will give into the
        hand of their enemies and into the hand of those who seek their lives, into
        the hand of the army of the king of Babylon which has withdrawn from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Behold, I will command, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and will bring them back to this city. And they will fight against it and
        take it and burn it with fire. I will make the cities of Judah a desolation
        without inhabitant.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Obedience of the Rechabites'
      title: The Obedience of the Rechabites
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the days of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to the house of the Rechabites and speak with them and bring
        them to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, into one of the chambers;
        then offer them wine to drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I took Jaazaniah the son of Jeremiah, son of Habazziniah and his
        brothers and all his sons and the whole house of the Rechabites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I brought them to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> into
        the chamber of the sons of Hanan the son of Igdaliah, the man of God, which
        was near the chamber of the officials, above the chamber of Maaseiah the
        son of Shallum, keeper of the threshold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I set before the Rechabites pitchers full of wine, and cups,
        and I said to them, \u201CDrink wine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But they answered, \u201CWe will drink no wine, for Jonadab the son
        of Rechab, our father, commanded us, \u2018You shall not drink wine, neither
        you nor your sons forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You shall not build a house; you shall not sow seed; you shall not
        plant or have a vineyard; but you shall live in tents all your days, that
        you may live many days in the land where you sojourn.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'We have obeyed the voice of Jonadab the son of Rechab, our father,
        in all that he commanded us, to drink no wine all our days, ourselves, our
        wives, our sons, or our daughters, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and not to build houses to dwell in. We have no vineyard or field
        or seed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but we have lived in tents and have obeyed and done all that Jonadab
        our father commanded us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But when Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against the land,
        we said, \u2018Come, and let us go to Jerusalem for fear of the army of the
        Chaldeans and the army of the Syrians.\u2019 So we are living in Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel: Go and say to the people of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem,
        Will you not receive instruction and listen to my words? declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The command that Jonadab the son of Rechab gave to his sons, to drink
        no wine, has been kept, and they drink none to this day, for they have obeyed
        their father\u2019s command. I have spoken to you persistently, but you have
        not listened to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I have sent to you all my servants the prophets, sending them persistently,
        saying, \u2018Turn now every one of you from his evil way, and amend your
        deeds, and do not go after other gods to serve them, and then you shall dwell
        in the land that I gave to you and your fathers.\u2019 But you did not incline
        your ear or listen to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sons of Jonadab the son of Rechab have kept the command that
        their father gave them, but this people has not obeyed me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore, thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, I am bringing upon Judah and all the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem all the disaster that I have pronounced against them, because
        I have spoken to them and they have not listened, I have called to them and
        they have not answered.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But to the house of the Rechabites Jeremiah said, \u201CThus says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel: Because you
        have obeyed the command of Jonadab your father and kept all his precepts
        and done all that he commanded you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the
        God of Israel: Jonadab the son of Rechab shall never lack a man to stand
        before me.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jehoiakim Burns Jeremiah\u2019s Scroll"
      title: "Jehoiakim Burns Jeremiah\u2019s Scroll"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah,
        this word came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake a scroll and write on it all the words that I have spoken
        to you against Israel and Judah and all the nations, from the day I spoke
        to you, from the days of Josiah until today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It may be that the house of Judah will hear all the disaster that
        I intend to do to them, so that every one may turn from his evil way, and
        that I may forgive their iniquity and their sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Jeremiah called Baruch the son of Neriah, and Baruch wrote on
        a scroll at the dictation of Jeremiah all the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that he had spoken to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Jeremiah ordered Baruch, saying, \u201CI am banned from going
        to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "so you are to go, and on a day of fasting in the hearing of all the
        people in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s house you shall read the
        words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> from the scroll that you have written
        at my dictation. You shall read them also in the hearing of all the men of
        Judah who come out of their cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "It may be that their plea for mercy will come before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and that every one will turn from his evil way, for great is the anger and
        wrath that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has pronounced against this people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Baruch the son of Neriah did all that Jeremiah the prophet ordered
        him about reading from the scroll the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  In the fifth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah,
        in the ninth month, all the people in Jerusalem and all the people who came
        from the cities of Judah to Jerusalem proclaimed a fast before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then, in the hearing of all the people, Baruch read the words of
        Jeremiah from the scroll, in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        in the chamber of Gemariah the son of Shaphan the secretary, which was in
        the upper court, at the entry of the New Gate of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Micaiah the son of Gemariah, son of Shaphan, heard all the words
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> from the scroll, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "he went down to the king\u2019s house, into the secretary\u2019s
        chamber, and all the officials were sitting there: Elishama the secretary,
        Delaiah the son of Shemaiah, Elnathan the son of Achbor, Gemariah the son
        of Shaphan, Zedekiah the son of Hananiah, and all the officials. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Micaiah told them all the words that he had heard, when Baruch
        read the scroll in the hearing of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then all the officials sent Jehudi the son of Nethaniah, son of Shelemiah,
        son of Cushi, to say to Baruch, \u201CTake in your hand the scroll that you
        read in the hearing of the people, and come.\u201D So Baruch the son of Neriah
        took the scroll in his hand and came to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CSit down and read it.\u201D So Baruch
        read it to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When they heard all the words, they turned one to another in fear.
        And they said to Baruch, \u201CWe must report all these words to the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then they asked Baruch, \u201CTell us, please, how did you write
        all these words? Was it at his dictation?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Baruch answered them, \u201CHe dictated all these words to me, while
        I wrote them with ink on the scroll.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the officials said to Baruch, \u201CGo and hide, you and Jeremiah,
        and let no one know where you are.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So they went into the court to the king, having put the scroll in
        the chamber of Elishama the secretary, and they reported all the words to
        the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the king sent Jehudi to get the scroll, and he took it from
        the chamber of Elishama the secretary. And Jehudi read it to the king and
        all the officials who stood beside the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It was the ninth month, and the king was sitting in the winter house,
        and there was a fire burning in the fire pot before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'As Jehudi read three or four columns, the king would cut them off
        with a knife and throw them into the fire in the fire pot, until the entire
        scroll was consumed in the fire that was in the fire pot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yet neither the king nor any of his servants who heard all these
        words was afraid, nor did they tear their garments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Even when Elnathan and Delaiah and Gemariah urged the king not to
        burn the scroll, he would not listen to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And the king commanded Jerahmeel the king\u2019s son and Seraiah
        the son of Azriel and Shelemiah the son of Abdeel to seize Baruch the secretary
        and Jeremiah the prophet, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> hid them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Now after the king had burned the scroll with the words that Baruch
        wrote at Jeremiah\u2019s dictation, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to Jeremiah: "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CTake another scroll and write on it all the former words that
        were in the first scroll, which Jehoiakim the king of Judah has burned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And concerning Jehoiakim king of Judah you shall say, \u2018Thus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, You have burned this scroll, saying,
        \u201CWhy have you written in it that the king of Babylon will certainly
        come and destroy this land, and will cut off from it man and beast?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning Jehoiakim
        king of Judah: He shall have none to sit on the throne of David, and his
        dead body shall be cast out to the heat by day and the frost by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And I will punish him and his offspring and his servants for their
        iniquity. I will bring upon them and upon the inhabitants of Jerusalem and
        upon the people of Judah all the disaster that I have pronounced against
        them, but they would not hear.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Then Jeremiah took another scroll and gave it to Baruch the scribe,
        the son of Neriah, who wrote on it at the dictation of Jeremiah all the words
        of the scroll that Jehoiakim king of Judah had burned in the fire. And many
        similar words were added to them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Warns Zedekiah'
      title: Jeremiah Warns Zedekiah
      number: 1
      content: '    Zedekiah the son of Josiah, whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon
        made king in the land of Judah, reigned instead of Coniah the son of Jehoiakim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But neither he nor his servants nor the people of the land listened
        to the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he spoke through Jeremiah
        the prophet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "King Zedekiah sent Jehucal the son of Shelemiah, and Zephaniah the
        priest, the son of Maaseiah, to Jeremiah the prophet, saying, \u201CPlease
        pray for us to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now Jeremiah was still going in and out among the people, for he
        had not yet been put in prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The army of Pharaoh had come out of Egypt. And when the Chaldeans
        who were besieging Jerusalem heard news about them, they withdrew from Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah
        the prophet: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of Israel: Thus
        shall you say to the king of Judah who sent you to me to inquire of me, \u2018Behold,
        Pharaoh\u2019s army that came to help you is about to return to Egypt, to
        its own land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Chaldeans shall come back and fight against this city. They
        shall capture it and burn it with fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Do not deceive yourselves,
        saying, \u201CThe Chaldeans will surely go away from us,\u201D for they will
        not go away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah Imprisoned'
      title: Jeremiah Imprisoned
      number: 10
      content: "For even if you should defeat the whole army of Chaldeans who are
        fighting against you, and there remained of them only wounded men, every
        man in his tent, they would rise up and burn this city with fire.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when the Chaldean army had withdrawn from Jerusalem at the approach
        of Pharaoh\u2019s army, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jeremiah set out from Jerusalem to go to the land of Benjamin to
        receive his portion there among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When he was at the Benjamin Gate, a sentry there named Irijah the
        son of Shelemiah, son of Hananiah, seized Jeremiah the prophet, saying, \u201CYou
        are deserting to the Chaldeans.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Jeremiah said, \u201CIt is a lie; I am not deserting to the Chaldeans.\u201D
        But Irijah would not listen to him, and seized Jeremiah and brought him to
        the officials. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the officials were enraged at Jeremiah, and they beat him and
        imprisoned him in the house of Jonathan the secretary, for it had been made
        a prison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  When Jeremiah had come to the dungeon cells and remained there
        many days, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "King Zedekiah sent for him and received him. The king questioned
        him secretly in his house and said, \u201CIs there any word from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D
        Jeremiah said, \u201CThere is.\u201D Then he said, \u201CYou shall be delivered
        into the hand of the king of Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jeremiah also said to King Zedekiah, \u201CWhat wrong have I done
        to you or your servants or this people, that you have put me in prison? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Where are your prophets who prophesied to you, saying, \u2018The
        king of Babylon will not come against you and against this land\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now hear, please, O my lord the king: let my humble plea come before
        you and do not send me back to the house of Jonathan the secretary, lest
        I die there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So King Zedekiah gave orders, and they committed Jeremiah to the
        court of the guard. And a loaf of bread was given him daily from the bakers\u2019
        street, until all the bread of the city was gone. So Jeremiah remained in
        the court of the guard."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Cast into the Cistern'
      title: Jeremiah Cast into the Cistern
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Shephatiah the son of Mattan, Gedaliah the son of Pashhur,
        Jucal the son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur the son of Malchiah heard the words
        that Jeremiah was saying to all the people: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: He who stays in
        this city shall die by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence, but he who
        goes out to the Chaldeans shall live. He shall have his life as a prize of
        war, and live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: This city shall surely
        be given into the hand of the army of the king of Babylon and be taken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the officials said to the king, \u201CLet this man be put to
        death, for he is weakening the hands of the soldiers who are left in this
        city, and the hands of all the people, by speaking such words to them. For
        this man is not seeking the welfare of this people, but their harm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "King Zedekiah said, \u201CBehold, he is in your hands, for the king
        can do nothing against you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Jeremiah Rescued from the Cistern'
      title: Jeremiah Rescued from the Cistern
      number: 6
      content: "So they took Jeremiah and cast him into the cistern of Malchiah,
        the king\u2019s son, which was in the court of the guard, letting Jeremiah
        down by ropes. And there was no water in the cistern, but only mud, and Jeremiah
        sank in the mud.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, a eunuch who was in the king\u2019s
        house, heard that they had put Jeremiah into the cistern\u2014the king was
        sitting in the Benjamin Gate\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ebed-melech went from the king\u2019s house and said to the king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CMy lord the king, these men have done evil in all that they
        did to Jeremiah the prophet by casting him into the cistern, and he will
        die there of hunger, for there is no bread left in the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king commanded Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, \u201CTake thirty
        men with you from here, and lift Jeremiah the prophet out of the cistern
        before he dies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Ebed-melech took the men with him and went to the house of the
        king, to a wardrobe in the storehouse, and took from there old rags and worn-out
        clothes, which he let down to Jeremiah in the cistern by ropes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Ebed-melech the Ethiopian said to Jeremiah, \u201CPut the rags
        and clothes between your armpits and the ropes.\u201D Jeremiah did so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jeremiah Warns Zedekiah Again'
      title: Jeremiah Warns Zedekiah Again
      number: 13
      content: 'Then they drew Jeremiah up with ropes and lifted him out of the cistern.
        And Jeremiah remained in the court of the guard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "King Zedekiah sent for Jeremiah the prophet and received him at the
        third entrance of the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. The king
        said to Jeremiah, \u201CI will ask you a question; hide nothing from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CIf I tell you, will you not surely
        put me to death? And if I give you counsel, you will not listen to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then King Zedekiah swore secretly to Jeremiah, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, who made our souls, I will not put you to death or deliver you into
        the hand of these men who seek your life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of hosts, the God of Israel: If you will surrender to the officials
        of the king of Babylon, then your life shall be spared, and this city shall
        not be burned with fire, and you and your house shall live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if you do not surrender to the officials of the king of Babylon,
        then this city shall be given into the hand of the Chaldeans, and they shall
        burn it with fire, and you shall not escape from their hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "King Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CI am afraid of the Judeans
        who have deserted to the Chaldeans, lest I be handed over to them and they
        deal cruelly with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jeremiah said, \u201CYou shall not be given to them. Obey now the
        voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in what I say to you, and it shall
        be well with you, and your life shall be spared. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if you refuse to surrender, this is the vision which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has shown to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Behold, all the women left in the house of the king of Judah were
        being led out to the officials of the king of Babylon and were saying,  \u201C\u2018Your
        trusted friends have deceived youand prevailed against you;now that your
        feet are sunk in the mud,they turn away from you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All your wives and your sons shall be led out to the Chaldeans, and
        you yourself shall not escape from their hand, but shall be seized by the
        king of Babylon, and this city shall be burned with fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CLet no one know of these words,
        and you shall not die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If the officials hear that I have spoken with you and come to you
        and say to you, \u2018Tell us what you said to the king and what the king
        said to you; hide nothing from us and we will not put you to death,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then you shall say to them, \u2018I made a humble plea to the king
        that he would not send me back to the house of Jonathan to die there.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then all the officials came to Jeremiah and asked him, and he answered
        them as the king had instructed him. So they stopped speaking with him, for
        the conversation had not been overheard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And Jeremiah remained in the court of the guard until the day that
        Jerusalem was taken.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '    In the ninth year of Zedekiah king of Judah, in the tenth month,
        Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and all his army came against Jerusalem and
        besieged it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In the eleventh year of Zedekiah, in the fourth month, on the ninth
        day of the month, a breach was made in the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then all the officials of the king of Babylon came and sat in the
        middle gate: Nergal-sar-ezer of Samgar, Nebu-sar-sekim the Rab-saris, Nergal-sar-ezer
        the Rab-mag, with all the rest of the officers of the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When Zedekiah king of Judah and all the soldiers saw them, they fled,
        going out of the city at night by way of the king\u2019s garden through the
        gate between the two walls; and they went toward the Arabah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued them and overtook Zedekiah
        in the plains of Jericho. And when they had taken him, they brought him up
        to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, at Riblah, in the land of Hamath; and
        he passed sentence on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The king of Babylon slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah at Riblah before
        his eyes, and the king of Babylon slaughtered all the nobles of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He put out the eyes of Zedekiah and bound him in chains to take him
        to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Chaldeans burned the king\u2019s house and the house of the people,
        and broke down the walls of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, carried into exile to
        Babylon the rest of the people who were left in the city, those who had deserted
        to him, and the people who remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The  Delivers Jeremiah'
      title: The  Delivers Jeremiah
      number: 10
      content: 'Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, left in the land of Judah
        some of the poor people who owned nothing, and gave them vineyards and fields
        at the same time.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon gave command concerning Jeremiah through
        Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTake him, look after him well, and do him no harm, but deal
        with him as he tells you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard, Nebushazban the Rab-saris,
        Nergal-sar-ezer the Rab-mag, and all the chief officers of the king of Babylon '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'sent and took Jeremiah from the court of the guard. They entrusted
        him to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan, that he should take him
        home. So he lived among the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah while
        he was shut up in the court of the guard: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CGo, and say to Ebed-melech the Ethiopian, \u2018Thus says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, I will fulfill
        my words against this city for harm and not for good, and they shall be accomplished
        before you on that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But I will deliver you on that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and you shall not be given into the hand of the men of whom you are afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For I will surely save you, and you shall not fall by the sword,
        but you shall have your life as a prize of war, because you have put your
        trust in me, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Remains in Judah'
      title: Jeremiah Remains in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        after Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had let him go from Ramah, when
        he took him bound in chains along with all the captives of Jerusalem and
        Judah who were being exiled to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The captain of the guard took Jeremiah and said to him, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God pronounced this disaster against this
        place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has brought it about, and has done
        as he said. Because you sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        did not obey his voice, this thing has come upon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now, behold, I release you today from the chains on your hands. If
        it seems good to you to come with me to Babylon, come, and I will look after
        you well, but if it seems wrong to you to come with me to Babylon, do not
        come. See, the whole land is before you; go wherever you think it good and
        right to go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "If you remain,[[COMMENT(0)]] then return to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam,
        son of Shaphan, whom the king of Babylon appointed governor of the cities
        of Judah, and dwell with him among the people. Or go wherever you think it
        right to go.\u201D So the captain of the guard gave him an allowance of food
        and a present, and let him go. "
      comments:
      - number: '40:5 '
        content: Syriac; the meaning of the Hebrew phrase is uncertain
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Jeremiah went to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, at Mizpah, and
        lived with him among the people who were left in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  When all the captains of the forces in the open country and their
        men heard that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam
        governor in the land and had committed to him men, women, and children, those
        of the poorest of the land who had not been taken into exile to Babylon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "they went to Gedaliah at Mizpah\u2014Ishmael the son of Nethaniah,
        Johanan the son of Kareah, Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth, the sons of Ephai
        the Netophathite, Jezaniah the son of the Maacathite, they and their men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan, swore to them and their
        men, saying, \u201CDo not be afraid to serve the Chaldeans. Dwell in the
        land and serve the king of Babylon, and it shall be well with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As for me, I will dwell at Mizpah, to represent you before the Chaldeans
        who will come to us. But as for you, gather wine and summer fruits and oil,
        and store them in your vessels, and dwell in your cities that you have taken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Likewise, when all the Judeans who were in Moab and among the Ammonites
        and in Edom and in other lands heard that the king of Babylon had left a
        remnant in Judah and had appointed Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan,
        as governor over them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'then all the Judeans returned from all the places to which they had
        been driven and came to the land of Judah, to Gedaliah at Mizpah. And they
        gathered wine and summer fruits in great abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now Johanan the son of Kareah and all the leaders of the forces in
        the open country came to Gedaliah at Mizpah '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and said to him, \u201CDo you know that Baalis the king of the Ammonites
        has sent Ishmael the son of Nethaniah to take your life?\u201D But Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam would not believe them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Johanan the son of Kareah spoke secretly to Gedaliah at Mizpah,
        \u201CPlease let me go and strike down Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and
        no one will know it. Why should he take your life, so that all the Judeans
        who are gathered about you would be scattered, and the remnant of Judah would
        perish?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam said to Johanan the son of Kareah,
        \u201CYou shall not do this thing, for you are speaking falsely of Ishmael.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Gedaliah Murdered'
      title: Gedaliah Murdered
      number: 1
      content: '    In the seventh month, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, son of Elishama,
        of the royal family, one of the chief officers of the king, came with ten
        men to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, at Mizpah. As they ate bread together
        there at Mizpah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ishmael the son of Nethaniah and the ten men with him rose up and
        struck down Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, son of Shaphan, with the sword, and
        killed him, whom the king of Babylon had appointed governor in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Ishmael also struck down all the Judeans who were with Gedaliah at
        Mizpah, and the Chaldean soldiers who happened to be there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the day after the murder of Gedaliah, before anyone knew of it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'eighty men arrived from Shechem and Shiloh and Samaria, with their
        beards shaved and their clothes torn, and their bodies gashed, bringing grain
        offerings and incense to present at the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Ishmael the son of Nethaniah came out from Mizpah to meet them,
        weeping as he came. As he met them, he said to them, \u201CCome in to Gedaliah
        the son of Ahikam.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When they came into the city, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah and the
        men with him slaughtered them and cast them into a cistern. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But there were ten men among them who said to Ishmael, \u201CDo not
        put us to death, for we have stores of wheat, barley, oil, and honey hidden
        in the fields.\u201D So he refrained and did not put them to death with their
        companions.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the cistern into which Ishmael had thrown all the bodies of the
        men whom he had struck down along with[[COMMENT(0)]] Gedaliah was the large
        cistern that King Asa had made for defense against Baasha king of Israel;
        Ishmael the son of Nethaniah filled it with the slain. '
      comments:
      - number: '41:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Ishmael took captive all the rest of the people who were in
        Mizpah, the king\u2019s daughters and all the people who were left at Mizpah,
        whom Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, had committed to Gedaliah the
        son of Ahikam. Ishmael the son of Nethaniah took them captive and set out
        to cross over to the Ammonites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when Johanan the son of Kareah and all the leaders of the forces
        with him heard of all the evil that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'they took all their men and went to fight against Ishmael the son
        of Nethaniah. They came upon him at the great pool that is in Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when all the people who were with Ishmael saw Johanan the son
        of Kareah and all the leaders of the forces with him, they rejoiced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So all the people whom Ishmael had carried away captive from Mizpah
        turned around and came back, and went to Johanan the son of Kareah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But Ishmael the son of Nethaniah escaped from Johanan with eight
        men, and went to the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Johanan the son of Kareah and all the leaders of the forces
        with him took from Mizpah all the rest of the people whom he had recovered
        from Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, after he had struck down Gedaliah the
        son of Ahikam\u2014soldiers, women, children, and eunuchs, whom Johanan brought
        back from Gibeon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And they went and stayed at Geruth Chimham near Bethlehem, intending
        to go to Egypt '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: because of the Chaldeans. For they were afraid of them, because Ishmael
        the son of Nethaniah had struck down Gedaliah the son of Ahikam, whom the
        king of Babylon had made governor over the land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Against Going to Egypt'
      title: Warning Against Going to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the commanders of the forces, and Johanan the son of Kareah
        and Jezaniah the son of Hoshaiah, and all the people from the least to the
        greatest, came near '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said to Jeremiah the prophet, \u201CLet our plea for mercy come
        before you, and pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God for us,
        for all this remnant\u2014because we are left with but a few, as your eyes
        see us\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God may show us the way
        we should go, and the thing that we should do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jeremiah the prophet said to them, \u201CI have heard you. Behold,
        I will pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God according to your
        request, and whatever the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answers you I will
        tell you. I will keep nothing back from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then they said to Jeremiah, \u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        be a true and faithful witness against us if we do not act according to all
        the word with which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God sends you to
        us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Whether it is good or bad, we will obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God to whom we are sending you, that it may be well with us when we obey
        the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  At the end of ten days the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he summoned Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders
        of the forces who were with him, and all the people from the least to the
        greatest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and said to them, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, to whom you sent me to present your plea for mercy before
        him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If you will remain in this land, then I will build you up and not
        pull you down; I will plant you, and not pluck you up; for I relent of the
        disaster that I did to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do not fear the king of Babylon, of whom you are afraid. Do not fear
        him, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for I am with you, to save
        you and to deliver you from his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will grant you mercy, that he may have mercy on you and let you
        remain in your own land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But if you say, \u2018We will not remain in this land,\u2019 disobeying
        the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and saying, \u2018No, we will go to the land of Egypt, where we shall
        not see war or hear the sound of the trumpet or be hungry for bread, and
        we will dwell there,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'then hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, O remnant
        of Judah. Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of
        Israel: If you set your faces to enter Egypt and go to live there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then the sword that you fear shall overtake you there in the land
        of Egypt, and the famine of which you are afraid shall follow close after
        you to Egypt, and there you shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All the men who set their faces to go to Egypt to live there shall
        die by the sword, by famine, and by pestilence. They shall have no remnant
        or survivor from the disaster that I will bring upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the
        God of Israel: As my anger and my wrath were poured out on the inhabitants
        of Jerusalem, so my wrath will be poured out on you when you go to Egypt.
        You shall become an execration, a horror, a curse, and a taunt. You shall
        see this place no more. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has said to you, O remnant of Judah,
        \u2018Do not go to Egypt.\u2019 Know for a certainty that I have warned you
        this day "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "that you have gone astray at the cost of your lives. For you sent
        me to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, saying, \u2018Pray for us
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, and whatever the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God says, declare to us and we will do it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And I have this day declared it to you, but you have not obeyed the
        voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God in anything that he sent
        me to tell you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now therefore know for a certainty that you shall die by the sword,
        by famine, and by pestilence in the place where you desire to go to live.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Taken to Egypt'
      title: Jeremiah Taken to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  When Jeremiah finished speaking to all the people all these words
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God, with which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God had sent him to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Azariah the son of Hoshaiah and Johanan the son of Kareah and all
        the insolent men said to Jeremiah, \u201CYou are telling a lie. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God did not send you to say, \u2018Do not go to Egypt to live there,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "but Baruch the son of Neriah has set you against us, to deliver us
        into the hand of the Chaldeans, that they may kill us or take us into exile
        in Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces
        and all the people did not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to remain in the land of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But Johanan the son of Kareah and all the commanders of the forces
        took all the remnant of Judah who had returned to live in the land of Judah
        from all the nations to which they had been driven\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'the men, the women, the children, the princesses, and every person
        whom Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard had left with Gedaliah the son
        of Ahikam, son of Shaphan; also Jeremiah the prophet and Baruch the son of
        Neriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And they came into the land of Egypt, for they did not obey the voice
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And they arrived at Tahpanhes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jeremiah
        in Tahpanhes: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTake in your hands large stones and hide them in the mortar
        in the pavement that is at the entrance to Pharaoh\u2019s palace in Tahpanhes,
        in the sight of the men of Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and say to them, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts, the God of Israel: Behold, I will send and take Nebuchadnezzar
        the king of Babylon, my servant, and I will set his throne above these stones
        that I have hidden, and he will spread his royal canopy over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He shall come and strike the land of Egypt, giving over to the pestilence
        those who are doomed to the pestilence, to captivity those who are doomed
        to captivity, and to the sword those who are doomed to the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I shall kindle a fire in the temples of the gods of Egypt, and he
        shall burn them and carry them away captive. And he shall clean the land
        of Egypt as a shepherd cleans his cloak of vermin, and he shall go away from
        there in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He shall break the obelisks of Heliopolis, which is in the land of
        Egypt, and the temples of the gods of Egypt he shall burn with fire.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment for Idolatry'
      title: Judgment for Idolatry
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that came to Jeremiah concerning all the Judeans who lived
        in the land of Egypt, at Migdol, at Tahpanhes, at Memphis, and in the land
        of Pathros, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God
        of Israel: You have seen all the disaster that I brought upon Jerusalem and
        upon all the cities of Judah. Behold, this day they are a desolation, and
        no one dwells in them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'because of the evil that they committed, provoking me to anger, in
        that they went to make offerings and serve other gods that they knew not,
        neither they, nor you, nor your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet I persistently sent to you all my servants the prophets, saying,
        \u2018Oh, do not do this abomination that I hate!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But they did not listen or incline their ear, to turn from their
        evil and make no offerings to other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore my wrath and my anger were poured out and kindled in the
        cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem, and they became a waste
        and a desolation, as at this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And now thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of hosts, the
        God of Israel: Why do you commit this great evil against yourselves, to cut
        off from you man and woman, infant and child, from the midst of Judah, leaving
        you no remnant? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Why do you provoke me to anger with the works of your hands, making
        offerings to other gods in the land of Egypt where you have come to live,
        so that you may be cut off and become a curse and a taunt among all the nations
        of the earth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you forgotten the evil of your fathers, the evil of the kings
        of Judah, the evil of their[[COMMENT(0)]] wives, your own evil, and the evil
        of your wives, which they committed in the land of Judah and in the streets
        of Jerusalem? '
      comments:
      - number: '44:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They have not humbled themselves even to this day, nor have they
        feared, nor walked in my law and my statutes that I set before you and before
        your fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts,
        the God of Israel: Behold, I will set my face against you for harm, to cut
        off all Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will take the remnant of Judah who have set their faces to come
        to the land of Egypt to live, and they shall all be consumed. In the land
        of Egypt they shall fall; by the sword and by famine they shall be consumed.
        From the least to the greatest, they shall die by the sword and by famine,
        and they shall become an oath, a horror, a curse, and a taunt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will punish those who dwell in the land of Egypt, as I have punished
        Jerusalem, with the sword, with famine, and with pestilence, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "so that none of the remnant of Judah who have come to live in the
        land of Egypt shall escape or survive or return to the land of Judah, to
        which they desire to return to dwell there. For they shall not return, except
        some fugitives.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then all the men who knew that their wives had made offerings to
        other gods, and all the women who stood by, a great assembly, all the people
        who lived in Pathros in the land of Egypt, answered Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAs for the word that you have spoken to us in the name of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, we will not listen to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But we will do everything that we have vowed, make offerings to the
        queen of heaven and pour out drink offerings to her, as we did, both we and
        our fathers, our kings and our officials, in the cities of Judah and in the
        streets of Jerusalem. For then we had plenty of food, and prospered, and
        saw no disaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But since we left off making offerings to the queen of heaven and
        pouring out drink offerings to her, we have lacked everything and have been
        consumed by the sword and by famine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the women said,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CWhen we made offerings to
        the queen of heaven and poured out drink offerings to her, was it without
        our husbands\u2019 approval that we made cakes for her bearing her image
        and poured out drink offerings to her?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '44:19 '
        content: 'Compare Syriac; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Jeremiah said to all the people, men and women, all the people
        who had given him this answer: '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAs for the offerings that you offered in the cities of Judah
        and in the streets of Jerusalem, you and your fathers, your kings and your
        officials, and the people of the land, did not the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        remember them? Did it not come into his mind? "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> could no longer bear your evil deeds
        and the abominations that you committed. Therefore your land has become a
        desolation and a waste and a curse, without inhabitant, as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "It is because you made offerings and because you sinned against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and did not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        or walk in his law and in his statutes and in his testimonies that this disaster
        has happened to you, as at this day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Jeremiah said to all the people and all the women, \u201CHear the
        word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all you of Judah who are in the
        land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel:
        You and your wives have declared with your mouths, and have fulfilled it
        with your hands, saying, \u2018We will surely perform our vows that we have
        made, to make offerings to the queen of heaven and to pour out drink offerings
        to her.\u2019 Then confirm your vows and perform your vows! "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all you
        of Judah who dwell in the land of Egypt: Behold, I have sworn by my great
        name, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that my name shall no more be
        invoked by the mouth of any man of Judah in all the land of Egypt, saying,
        \u2018As the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> lives.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Behold, I am watching over them for disaster and not for good. All
        the men of Judah who are in the land of Egypt shall be consumed by the sword
        and by famine, until there is an end of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And those who escape the sword shall return from the land of Egypt
        to the land of Judah, few in number; and all the remnant of Judah, who came
        to the land of Egypt to live, shall know whose word will stand, mine or theirs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'This shall be the sign to you, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that I will punish you in this place, in order that you may know that my
        words will surely stand against you for harm: '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Behold, I will give Pharaoh
        Hophra king of Egypt into the hand of his enemies and into the hand of those
        who seek his life, as I gave Zedekiah king of Judah into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar
        king of Babylon, who was his enemy and sought his life.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Message to Baruch'
      title: Message to Baruch
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that Jeremiah the prophet spoke to Baruch the son of Neriah,
        when he wrote these words in a book at the dictation of Jeremiah, in the
        fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king of Judah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        to you, O Baruch: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You said, \u2018Woe is me! For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        added sorrow to my pain. I am weary with my groaning, and I find no rest.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus shall you say to him, Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        Behold, what I have built I am breaking down, and what I have planted I am
        plucking up\u2014that is, the whole land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And do you seek great things for yourself? Seek them not, for behold,
        I am bringing disaster upon all flesh, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        But I will give you your life as a prize of war in all places to which you
        may go.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Egypt'
      title: Judgment on Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that came to Jeremiah
        the prophet concerning the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'About Egypt. Concerning the army of Pharaoh Neco, king of Egypt,
        which was by the river Euphrates at Carchemish and which Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon defeated in the fourth year of Jehoiakim the son of Josiah, king
        of Judah:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  \u201CPrepare buckler and shield,and advance for battle!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Harness the horses;mount, O horsemen!Take your stations with your
        helmets,  polish your spears,put on your armor!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Why have I seen it?They are dismayedand have turned backward.Their
        warriors are beaten downand have fled in haste;  they look not back\u2014 
        terror on every side!declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThe swift cannot flee away,nor the warrior escape;  in the
        north by the river Euphrates  they have stumbled and fallen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWho is this, rising like the Nile,like rivers whose waters
        surge?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Egypt rises like the Nile,like rivers whose waters surge.He said,
        \u2018I will rise, I will cover the earth,I will destroy cities and their
        inhabitants.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Advance, O horses,and rage, O chariots!Let the warriors go out:men
        of Cush and Put who handle the shield,  men of Lud, skilled in handling the
        bow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  That day is the day of the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts, 
        a day of vengeance,  to avenge himself on his foes.  The sword shall devour
        and be satedand drink its fill of their blood.For the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        of hosts holds a sacrifice  in the north country by the river Euphrates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Go up to Gilead, and take balm,O virgin daughter of Egypt!In vain
        you have used many medicines;  there is no healing for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The nations have heard of your shame,and the earth is full of your
        cry;  for warrior has stumbled against warrior;they have both fallen together.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Jeremiah the
        prophet about the coming of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon to strike the
        land of Egypt:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CDeclare in Egypt, and proclaim in Migdol;proclaim in Memphis
        and Tahpanhes;say, \u2018Stand ready and be prepared,for the sword shall
        devour around you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Why are your mighty ones face down?They do not stand[[COMMENT(0)]]because
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> thrust them down.  '
      comments:
      - number: '46:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He made many stumble, and they fell,and they said one to another,\u2018Arise,
        and let us go back to our own peopleand to the land of our birth,  because
        of the sword of the oppressor.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Call the name of Pharaoh, king of Egypt,\u2018Noisy one who lets
        the hour go by.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201CAs I live, declares the King,  whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts,like Tabor among the mountainsand like Carmel by the sea, shall
        one come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Prepare yourselves baggage for exile,O inhabitants of Egypt!For
        Memphis shall become a waste,a ruin, without inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CA beautiful heifer is Egypt,but a biting fly from the north
        has come upon her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Even her hired soldiers in her midstare like fattened calves;yes,
        they have turned and fled together;they did not stand,for the day of their
        calamity has come upon them,  the time of their punishment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CShe makes a sound like a serpent gliding away;for her enemies
        march in forceand come against her with axes  like those who fell trees.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  They shall cut down her forest,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,though
        it is impenetrable,because they are more numerous than locusts;they are without
        number.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The daughter of Egypt shall be put to shame;she shall be delivered
        into the hand of a people from the north.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of Israel, said:
        \u201CBehold, I am bringing punishment upon Amon of Thebes, and Pharaoh and
        Egypt and her gods and her kings, upon Pharaoh and those who trust in him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will deliver them into the hand of those who seek their life, into
        the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and his officers. Afterward Egypt
        shall be inhabited as in the days of old, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  \u201CBut fear not, O Jacob my servant,nor be dismayed, O Israel,for
        behold, I will save you from far away,and your offspring from the land of
        their captivity.Jacob shall return and have quiet and ease,and none shall
        make him afraid.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  Fear not, O Jacob my servant,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for
        I am with you.I will make a full end of all the nationsto which I have driven
        you,but of you I will not make a full end.  I will discipline you in just
        measure,and I will by no means leave you unpunished.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on the Philistines'
      title: Judgment on the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that came to Jeremiah
        the prophet concerning the Philistines, before Pharaoh struck down Gaza.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  Behold, waters
        are rising out of the north,  and shall become an overflowing torrent;they
        shall overflow the land and all that fills it,the city and those who dwell
        in it.Men shall cry out,and every inhabitant of the land shall wail.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'At the noise of the stamping of the hoofs of his stallions,  at the
        rushing of his chariots, at the rumbling of their wheels,the fathers look
        not back to their children,so feeble are their hands,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'because of the day that is coming to destroyall the Philistines,to
        cut off from Tyre and Sidonevery helper that remains.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is destroying the Philistines,  the remnant of the coastland of Caphtor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Baldness has come upon Gaza;  Ashkelon has perished.O remnant of
        their valley,  how long will you gash yourselves?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Ah, sword of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!How long till you
        are quiet?Put yourself into your scabbard;rest and be still!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How can it[[COMMENT(0)]] be quiet  when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given it a charge?Against Ashkelon and against the seashore  he has appointed
        it.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '47:7 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Moab'
      title: Judgment on Moab
      number: 1
      content: "    Concerning Moab.Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        hosts, the God of Israel:\u201CWoe to Nebo, for it is laid waste!  Kiriathaim
        is put to shame, it is taken;the fortress is put to shame and broken down;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "the renown of Moab is no more.In Heshbon they planned disaster against
        her:\u2018Come, let us cut her off from being a nation!\u2019You also, O
        Madmen, shall be brought to silence;the sword shall pursue you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CA voice! A cry from Horonaim,\u2018Desolation and great destruction!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moab is destroyed;her little ones have made a cry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  For at the ascent of Luhiththey go up weeping;[[COMMENT(0)]]for
        at the descent of Horonaimthey have heard the distressed cry of destruction.  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew Septuagint (compare Isaiah 15:5) '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Flee! Save yourselves!You will be like a juniper in the desert!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For, because you trusted in your works and your treasures,you also
        shall be taken;and Chemosh shall go into exilewith his priests and his officials.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The destroyer shall come upon every city,and no city shall escape;the
        valley shall perish,and the plain shall be destroyed,as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CGive wings to Moab,for she would fly away;her cities shall
        become a desolation,with no inhabitant in them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  \u201CCursed is he who does the work of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with slackness, and cursed is he who keeps back his sword from bloodshed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CMoab has been at ease from his youthand has settled on his
        dregs;he has not been emptied from vessel to vessel,nor has he gone into
        exile;so his taste remains in him,and his scent is not changed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when I shall send to him pourers who will pour him, and empty his vessels
        and break his[[COMMENT(0)]] jars in pieces. "
      comments:
      - number: '48:12 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Aquila; Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Moab shall be ashamed of Chemosh, as the house of Israel was
        ashamed of Bethel, their confidence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CHow do you say, \u2018We are heroesand mighty men of war\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The destroyer of Moab and his cities has come up,and the choicest
        of his young men have gone down to slaughter,declares the King, whose name
        is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The calamity of Moab is near at hand,and his affliction hastens swiftly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  Grieve for him, all you who are around him,and all who know his
        name;say, \u2018How the mighty scepter is broken,the glorious staff.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "  \u201CCome down from your glory,and sit on the parched ground,O
        inhabitant of Dibon!For the destroyer of Moab has come up against you;he
        has destroyed your strongholds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  Stand by the way and watch,O inhabitant of Aroer!Ask him who flees
        and her who escapes;say, \u2018What has happened?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Moab is put to shame, for it is broken;  wail and cry!Tell it beside
        the Arnon,that Moab is laid waste.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CJudgment has come upon the tableland, upon Holon, and Jahzah,
        and Mephaath, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Dibon, and Nebo, and Beth-diblathaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and Kiriathaim, and Beth-gamul, and Beth-meon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and Kerioth, and Bozrah, and all the cities of the land of Moab,
        far and near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The horn of Moab is cut off, and his arm is broken, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201CMake him drunk, because he magnified himself against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, so that Moab shall wallow in his vomit, and
        he too shall be held in derision. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Was not Israel a derision to you? Was he found among thieves, that
        whenever you spoke of him you wagged your head?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  \u201CLeave the cities, and dwell in the rock,O inhabitants of
        Moab!Be like the dove that nestsin the sides of the mouth of a gorge.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  We have heard of the pride of Moab\u2014he is very proud\u2014of
        his loftiness, his pride, and his arrogance,and the haughtiness of his heart.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I know his insolence, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        his boasts are false,his deeds are false.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  Therefore I wail for Moab;I cry out for all Moab;for the men of
        Kir-hareseth I mourn.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'More than for Jazer I weep for you,  O vine of Sibmah!  Your branches
        passed over the sea,reached to the Sea of Jazer;on your summer fruits and
        your grapesthe destroyer has fallen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  Gladness and joy have been taken awayfrom the fruitful land of
        Moab;I have made the wine cease from the winepresses;no one treads them with
        shouts of joy;the shouting is not the shout of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "  \u201CFrom the outcry at Heshbon even to Elealeh, as far as Jahaz
        they utter their voice, from Zoar to Horonaim and Eglath-shelishiyah. For
        the waters of Nimrim also have become desolate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And I will bring to an end in Moab, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        him who offers sacrifice in the high place and makes offerings to his god. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Therefore my heart moans for Moab like a flute, and my heart moans
        like a flute for the men of Kir-hareseth. Therefore the riches they gained
        have perished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  \u201CFor every head is shaved and every beard cut off. On all
        the hands are gashes, and around the waist is sackcloth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'On all the housetops of Moab and in the squares there is nothing
        but lamentation, for I have broken Moab like a vessel for which no one cares,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "How it is broken! How they wail! How Moab has turned his back in
        shame! So Moab has become a derision and a horror to all that are around
        him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CBehold, one shall
        fly swiftly like an eagle  and spread his wings against Moab;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '  the cities shall be takenand the strongholds seized.  The heart
        of the warriors of Moab shall be in that daylike the heart of a woman in
        her birth pains;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Moab shall be destroyed and be no longer a people,because he magnified
        himself against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '  Terror, pit, and snareare before you, O inhabitant of Moab!declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'He who flees from the terrorshall fall into the pit,and he who climbs
        out of the pitshall be caught in the snare.  For I will bring these things
        upon Moab,the year of their punishment,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CIn the shadow of Heshbonfugitives stop without strength,for
        fire came out from Heshbon,flame from the house of Sihon;it has destroyed
        the forehead of Moab,the crown of the sons of tumult.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: '  Woe to you, O Moab!The people of Chemosh are undone,for your sons
        have been taken captive,and your daughters into captivity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "  Yet I will restore the fortunes of Moabin the latter days, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201DThus far is the judgment on Moab."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Ammon'
      title: Judgment on Ammon
      number: 1
      content: "    Concerning the Ammonites.Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CHas
        Israel no sons?Has he no heir?Why then has Milcom[[COMMENT(0)]]  dispossessed
        Gad,and his people settled in its cities?  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:1 '
        content: Or ; also verse 3
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Therefore, behold, the days are coming,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,when
        I will cause the battle cry to be heardagainst Rabbah of the Ammonites;it
        shall become a desolate mound,and its villages shall be burned with fire;then
        Israel shall dispossess those who dispossessed him,says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CWail, O Heshbon, for Ai is laid waste!Cry out, O daughters
        of Rabbah!  Put on sackcloth,lament, and run to and fro among the hedges!For
        Milcom shall go into exile,  with his priests and his officials.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Why do you boast of your valleys,[[COMMENT(0)]]  O faithless daughter, 
        who trusted in her treasures, saying,\u2018Who will come against me?\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Behold, I will bring terror upon you,declares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        of hosts,from all who are around you,and you shall be driven out, every man
        straight before him,with none to gather the fugitives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Judgment on Edom'
      title: Judgment on Edom
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBut afterward I will restore the fortunes of the Ammonites,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Concerning Edom.Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: 
        \u201CIs wisdom no more in Teman?  Has counsel perished from the prudent? 
        Has their wisdom vanished?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Flee, turn back, dwell in the depths,O inhabitants of Dedan!For
        I will bring the calamity of Esau upon him,  the time when I punish him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  If grape gatherers came to you,would they not leave gleanings? 
        If thieves came by night,would they not destroy only enough for themselves?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  But I have stripped Esau bare;  I have uncovered his hiding places,and
        he is not able to conceal himself.His children are destroyed, and his brothers,and
        his neighbors; and he is no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  Leave your fatherless children; I will keep them alive;  and let
        your widows trust in me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CIf those who
        did not deserve to drink the cup must drink it, will you go unpunished? You
        shall not go unpunished, but you must drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I have sworn by myself, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        that Bozrah shall become a horror, a taunt, a waste, and a curse, and all
        her cities shall be perpetual wastes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  I have heard a message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        an envoy has been sent among the nations:  \u201CGather yourselves together
        and come against her,and rise up for battle!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For behold, I will make you small among the nations,despised among
        mankind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The horror you inspire has deceived you,and the pride of your heart,you
        who live in the clefts of the rock,[[COMMENT(0)]]who hold the height of the
        hill.Though you make your nest as high as the eagle\u2019s,I will bring you
        down from there,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CEdom shall become a horror. Everyone who passes by it will
        be horrified and will hiss because of all its disasters. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'As when Sodom and Gomorrah and their neighboring cities were overthrown,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, no man shall dwell there, no man shall
        sojourn in her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Behold, like a lion coming up from the jungle of the Jordan against
        a perennial pasture, I will suddenly make him[[COMMENT(0)]] run away from
        her. And I will appoint over her whomever I choose. For who is like me? Who
        will summon me? What shepherd can stand before me? '
      comments:
      - number: '49:19 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Therefore hear the plan that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        made against Edom and the purposes that he has formed against the inhabitants
        of Teman: Even the little ones of the flock shall be dragged away. Surely
        their fold shall be appalled at their fate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'At the sound of their fall the earth shall tremble; the sound of
        their cry shall be heard at the Red Sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Judgment on Damascus'
      title: Judgment on Damascus
      number: 22
      content: "Behold, one shall mount up and fly swiftly like an eagle and spread
        his wings against Bozrah, and the heart of the warriors of Edom shall be
        in that day like the heart of a woman in her birth pains.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Concerning Damascus:  \u201CHamath and Arpad are confounded,for they
        have heard bad news;they melt in fear,  they are troubled like the sea that
        cannot be quiet.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Damascus has become feeble, she turned to flee,and panic seized
        her;anguish and sorrows have taken hold of her,as of a woman in labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'How is the famous city not forsaken,the city of my joy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  Therefore her young men shall fall in her squares,and all her soldiers
        shall be destroyed in that day,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Judgment on Kedar and Hazor'
      title: Judgment on Kedar and Hazor
      number: 27
      content: "And I will kindle a fire in the wall of Damascus,and it shall devour
        the strongholds of Ben-hadad.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Concerning Kedar and the kingdoms of Hazor that Nebuchadnezzar king
        of Babylon struck down.Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  \u201CRise
        up, advance against Kedar!Destroy the people of the east!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  Their tents and their flocks shall be taken,their curtains and
        all their goods;their camels shall be led away from them,and men shall cry
        to them: \u2018Terror on every side!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  Flee, wander far away, dwell in the depths,O inhabitants of Hazor!declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.For Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylonhas made
        a plan against youand formed a purpose against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "  \u201CRise up, advance against a nation at ease,  that dwells securely,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  that has no gates or bars,that dwells alone.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  Their camels shall become plunder,their herds of livestock a spoil. 
        I will scatter to every wind  those who cut the corners of their hair,and
        I will bring their calamityfrom every side of them,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Judgment on Elam'
      title: Judgment on Elam
      number: 33
      content: "Hazor shall become a haunt of jackals,an everlasting waste;  no man
        shall dwell there;  no man shall sojourn in her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'The word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that came to Jeremiah
        the prophet concerning Elam, in the beginning of the reign of Zedekiah king
        of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: \u201CBehold,
        I will break the bow of Elam, the mainstay of their might. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And I will bring upon Elam the four winds from the four quarters
        of heaven. And I will scatter them to all those winds, and there shall be
        no nation to which those driven out of Elam shall not come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I will terrify Elam before their enemies and before those who seek
        their life. I will bring disaster upon them, my fierce anger, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. I will send the sword after them, until I have
        consumed them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and I will set my throne in Elam and destroy their king and officials,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CBut in the latter days I will restore the fortunes of Elam,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Babylon'
      title: Judgment on Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke concerning
        Babylon, concerning the land of the Chaldeans, by Jeremiah the prophet:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDeclare among the nations and proclaim,set up a banner and
        proclaim,conceal it not, and say:  \u2018Babylon is taken,  Bel is put to
        shame,Merodach is dismayed.  Her images are put to shame,her idols are dismayed.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CFor out of the north a nation has come up against her, which
        shall make her land a desolation, and none shall dwell in it; both man and
        beast shall flee away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CIn those days and in that time, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the people of Israel and the people of Judah shall come together, weeping
        as they come, and they shall seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They shall ask the way to Zion, with faces turned toward it, saying,
        \u2018Come, let us join ourselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in an
        everlasting covenant that will never be forgotten.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CMy people have been lost sheep. Their shepherds have led
        them astray, turning them away on the mountains. From mountain to hill they
        have gone. They have forgotten their fold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All who found them have devoured them, and their enemies have said,
        \u2018We are not guilty, for they have sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        their habitation of righteousness, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the hope
        of their fathers.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  \u201CFlee from the midst of Babylon, and go out of the land of
        the Chaldeans, and be as male goats before the flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For behold, I am stirring up and bringing against Babylon a gathering
        of great nations, from the north country. And they shall array themselves
        against her. From there she shall be taken. Their arrows are like a skilled
        warrior who does not return empty-handed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Chaldea shall be plundered; all who plunder her shall be sated, declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  \u201CThough you rejoice, though you exult,O plunderers of my heritage,though
        you frolic like a heifer in the pasture,and neigh like stallions,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'your mother shall be utterly shamed,and she who bore you shall be
        disgraced.Behold, she shall be the last of the nations,  a wilderness, a
        dry land, and a desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Because of the wrath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> she shall
        not be inhabitedbut shall be an utter desolation;  everyone who passes by
        Babylon shall be appalled,  and hiss because of all her wounds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Set yourselves in array against Babylon all around,  all you who
        bend the bow;shoot at her, spare no arrows,  for she has sinned against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Raise a shout against her all around;she has surrendered;her bulwarks
        have fallen;  her walls are thrown down.For this is the vengeance of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:take vengeance on her;  do to her as she has
        done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Cut off from Babylon the sower,and the one who handles the sickle
        in time of harvest;  because of the sword of the oppressor,  every one shall
        turn to his own people,and every one shall flee to his own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CIsrael is a hunted sheep driven away by lions. First the
        king of Assyria devoured him, and now at last Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon
        has gnawed his bones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore, thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the
        God of Israel: Behold, I am bringing punishment on the king of Babylon and
        his land, as I punished the king of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will restore Israel to his pasture, and he shall feed on Carmel
        and in Bashan, and his desire shall be satisfied on the hills of Ephraim
        and in Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In those days and in that time, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        iniquity shall be sought in Israel, and there shall be none, and sin in Judah,
        and none shall be found, for I will pardon those whom I leave as a remnant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CGo up against the land of Merathaim,[[COMMENT(0)]]and against
        the inhabitants of Pekod.Kill, and devote them to destruction,declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and do all that I have commanded you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '50:21 '
        content: means means That is, set apart (devote) as an offering to the Lord
          (for destruction)
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The noise of battle is in the land,and great destruction!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  How the hammer of the whole earthis cut down and broken!  How Babylon
        has becomea horror among the nations!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  I set a snare for you and you were taken, O Babylon,and you did
        not know it;you were found and caught,because you opposed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has opened his armoryand brought
        out the weapons of his wrath,for the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps> of hosts
        has a work to doin the land of the Chaldeans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Come against her from every quarter;open her granaries;  pile her
        up like heaps of grain, and devote her to destruction;let nothing be left
        of her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Kill all her bulls;let them go down to the slaughter.Woe to them,
        for their day has come,  the time of their punishment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CA voice! They flee and escape from the land of Babylon, to
        declare in Zion the vengeance of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God,
        vengeance for his temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  \u201CSummon archers against Babylon, all those who bend the bow.
        Encamp around her; let no one escape. Repay her according to her deeds; do
        to her according to all that she has done. For she has proudly defied the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Holy One of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Therefore her young men shall fall in her squares, and all her soldiers
        shall be destroyed on that day, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am against you, O proud one,declares the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        of hosts,  for your day has come,the time when I will punish you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  The proud one shall stumble and fall,with none to raise him up, 
        and I will kindle a fire in his cities,and it will devour all that is around
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts: The people
        of Israel are oppressed, and the people of Judah with them. All who took
        them captive have held them fast; they refuse to let them go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Their Redeemer is strong; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts
        is his name. He will surely plead their cause, that he may give rest to the
        earth, but unrest to the inhabitants of Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CA sword against the Chaldeans, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        against the inhabitants of Babylon,and against her officials and her wise
        men!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'A sword against the diviners,that they may become fools!A sword against
        her warriors,that they may be destroyed!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'A sword against her horses and against her chariots,and against all
        the foreign troops in her midst,that they may become women!  A sword against
        all her treasures,that they may be plundered!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '  A drought against her waters,that they may be dried up!  For it
        is a land of images,and they are mad over idols.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "  \u201CTherefore wild beasts shall dwell with hyenas in Babylon,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and ostriches shall dwell in her. She shall never again have people, nor
        be inhabited for all generations. "
      comments:
      - number: '50:39 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'As when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah and their neighboring cities,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, so no man shall dwell there, and
        no son of man shall sojourn in her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "  \u201CBehold, a people comes from the north;a mighty nation and
        many kingsare stirring from the farthest parts of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They lay hold of bow and spear;they are cruel and have no mercy.The
        sound of them is like the roaring of the sea;they ride on horses,arrayed
        as a man for battleagainst you, O daughter of Babylon!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "\u201CThe king of Babylon heard the report of them,and his hands
        fell helpless;anguish seized him,pain as of a woman in labor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "  \u201CBehold, like a lion coming up from the thicket of the Jordan
        against a perennial pasture, I will suddenly make them run away from her,
        and I will appoint over her whomever I choose. For who is like me? Who will
        summon me? What shepherd can stand before me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Therefore hear the plan that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        made against Babylon, and the purposes that he has formed against the land
        of the Chaldeans: Surely the little ones of their flock shall be dragged
        away; surely their fold shall be appalled at their fate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "At the sound of the capture of Babylon the earth shall tremble, and
        her cry shall be heard among the nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Utter Destruction of Babylon'
      title: The Utter Destruction of Babylon
      number: 1
      content: "  Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CBehold, I will
        stir up the spirit of a destroyeragainst Babylon,against the inhabitants
        of Leb-kamai,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:1 '
        content: A code name for Chaldea
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and I will send to Babylon winnowers,and they shall winnow her,and
        they shall empty her land,when they come against her from every side  on
        the day of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Let not the archer bend his bow,and let him not stand up in his
        armor.Spare not her young men;  devote to destruction[[COMMENT(0)]] all her
        army.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:3 '
        content: That is, set apart (devote) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They shall fall down slain in the land of the Chaldeans,  and wounded
        in her streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  For Israel and Judah have not been forsakenby their God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts,but the land of the Chaldeans[[COMMENT(0)]] is full of guiltagainst
        the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  \u201CFlee from the midst of Babylon;let every one save his life! 
        Be not cut off in her punishment,  for this is the time of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        vengeance,the repayment he is rendering her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Babylon was a golden cup in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        hand,  making all the earth drunken;  the nations drank of her wine;therefore
        the nations went mad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Suddenly Babylon has fallen and been broken;  wail for her!  Take
        balm for her pain;perhaps she may be healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We would have healed Babylon,but she was not healed.  Forsake her,
        and let us goeach to his own country,for her judgment has reached up to heavenand
        has been lifted up even to the skies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has brought about our vindication; 
        come, let us declare in Zionthe work of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  \u201CSharpen the arrows!Take up the shields!  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has stirred up the spirit of the kings of the Medes, because his purpose
        concerning Babylon is to destroy it, for that is the vengeance of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the vengeance for his temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  \u201CSet up a standard against the walls of Babylon;  make the
        watch strong;set up watchmen;prepare the ambushes;  for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has both planned and donewhat he spoke concerning the inhabitants of Babylon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  O you who dwell by many waters,rich in treasures,your end has come;the
        thread of your life is cut.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts has sworn by himself:Surely
        I will fill you with men, as many as locusts,  and they shall raise the shout
        of victory over you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  \u201CIt is he who made the earth by his power,who established
        the world by his wisdom,and by his understanding stretched out the heavens.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When he utters his voice there is a tumult of waters in the heavens,and
        he makes the mist rise from the ends of the earth.He makes lightning for
        the rain,and he brings forth the wind from his storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Every man is stupid and without knowledge;every goldsmith is put
        to shame by his idols,for his images are false,and there is no breath in
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They are worthless, a work of delusion;at the time of their punishment
        they shall perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Not like these is he who is the portion of Jacob,for he is the one
        who formed all things,and Israel is the tribe of his inheritance;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of hosts is his name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CYou are my hammer and weapon of war:with you I break nations
        in pieces;with you I destroy kingdoms;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'with you I break in pieces the horse and his rider;with you I break
        in pieces the chariot and the charioteer;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'with you I break in pieces man and woman;with you I break in pieces
        the old man and the youth;with you I break in pieces the young man and the
        young woman;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'with you I break in pieces the shepherd and his flock;with you I
        break in pieces the farmer and his team;with you I break in pieces governors
        and commanders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201CI will repay Babylon and all the inhabitants of Chaldea before
        your very eyes for all the evil that they have done in Zion, declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am against you, O destroying mountain,declares the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,which destroys the whole earth;I will stretch
        out my hand against you,and roll you down from the crags,  and make you a
        burnt mountain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'No stone shall be taken from you for a cornerand no stone for a foundation,but
        you shall be a perpetual waste,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  \u201CSet up a standard on the earth;  blow the trumpet among the
        nations;  prepare the nations for war against her;summon against her the
        kingdoms,  Ararat, Minni, and Ashkenaz;appoint a marshal against her;  bring
        up horses like bristling locusts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  Prepare the nations for war against her,the kings of the Medes,
        with their governors and deputies,and every land under their dominion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "  The land trembles and writhes in pain,  for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        purposes against Babylon stand,to make the land of Babylon a desolation,without
        inhabitant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The warriors of Babylon have ceased fighting;they remain in their
        strongholds;their strength has failed;  they have become women;  her dwellings
        are on fire;  her bars are broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'One runner runs to meet another,and one messenger to meet another,to
        tell the king of Babylonthat his city is taken on every side;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'the fords have been seized,the marshes are burned with fire,and the
        soldiers are in panic.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts, the God of
        Israel:  The daughter of Babylon is like a threshing floorat the time when
        it is trodden;yet a little whileand the time of her harvest will come.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CNebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon has devoured me;he has crushed
        me;he has made me an empty vessel;  he has swallowed me like a monster;he
        has filled his stomach with my delicacies;he has rinsed me out.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:34 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "The violence done to me and to my kinsmen be upon Babylon,\u201Dlet
        the inhabitant of Zion say.\u201CMy blood be upon the inhabitants of Chaldea,\u201Dlet
        Jerusalem say.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Therefore thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CBehold,
        I will plead your causeand take vengeance for you.  I will dry up her seaand
        make her fountain dry,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and Babylon shall become a heap of ruins,  the haunt of jackals, 
        a horror and a hissing,without inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "  \u201CThey shall roar together like lions;they shall growl like
        lions\u2019 cubs.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: '  While they are inflamed I will prepare them a feastand make them
        drunk, that they may become merry,  then sleep a perpetual sleepand not wake,
        declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'I will bring them down like lambs to the slaughter,like rams and
        male goats.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CHow Babylon[[COMMENT(0)]] is taken,  the praise of the whole
        earth seized!How Babylon has becomea horror among the nations!  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:41 '
        content: Hebrew , a code name for Babylon
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '  The sea has come up on Babylon;she is covered with its tumultuous
        waves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Her cities have become a horror,  a land of drought and a desert, 
        a land in which no one dwells,and through which no son of man passes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And I will punish Bel in Babylon,and take out of his mouth what he
        has swallowed.  The nations shall no longer flow to him;  the wall of Babylon
        has fallen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CGo out of the midst of her, my people!Let every one save his
        lifefrom the fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Let not your heart faint, and be not fearful  at the report heard
        in the land,  when a report comes in one yearand afterward a report in another
        year,and violence is in the land,  and ruler is against ruler.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, the days are comingwhen I will punish the
        images of Babylon;  her whole land shall be put to shame,and all her slain
        shall fall in the midst of her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: '  Then the heavens and the earth,and all that is in them,shall sing
        for joy over Babylon,  for the destroyers shall come against them out of
        the north,declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Babylon must fall for the slain of Israel,  just as for Babylon have
        fallen the slain of all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "  \u201CYou who have escaped from the sword,go, do not stand still!Remember
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> from far away,and let Jerusalem come into
        your mind:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "  \u2018We are put to shame, for we have heard reproach;  dishonor
        has covered our face,  for foreigners have comeinto the holy places of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s house.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, the days are coming, declares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,when
        I will execute judgment upon her images,  and through all her landthe wounded
        shall groan.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Though Babylon should mount up to heaven,and though she should fortify
        her strong height,yet destroyers would come from me against her,declares
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "  \u201CA voice! A cry from Babylon!The noise of great destruction
        from the land of the Chaldeans!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is laying Babylon wasteand stilling
        her mighty voice.  Their waves roar like many waters;the noise of their voice
        is raised,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'for a destroyer has come upon her,upon Babylon;her warriors are taken;their
        bows are broken in pieces,  for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a God
        of recompense;he will surely repay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: '  I will make drunk her officials and her wise men,  her governors,
        her commanders, and her warriors;they shall sleep a perpetual sleep and not
        wake,declares the King, whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        hosts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "\u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts:The broad
        wall of Babylonshall be leveled to the ground,  and her high gatesshall be
        burned with fire.  The peoples labor for nothing,and the nations weary themselves
        only for fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'The word that Jeremiah the prophet commanded Seraiah the son of Neriah,
        son of Mahseiah, when he went with Zedekiah king of Judah to Babylon, in
        the fourth year of his reign. Seraiah was the quartermaster. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'Jeremiah wrote in a book all the disaster that should come upon Babylon,
        all these words that are written concerning Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "And Jeremiah said to Seraiah: \u201CWhen you come to Babylon, see
        that you read all these words, "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "and say, \u2018O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you have said concerning
        this place that you will cut it off, so that nothing shall dwell in it, neither
        man nor beast, and it shall be desolate forever.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'When you finish reading this book, tie a stone to it and cast it
        into the midst of the Euphrates, '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus shall Babylon sink, to rise no more, because
        of the disaster that I am bringing upon her, and they shall become exhausted.\u2019\u201DThus
        far are the words of Jeremiah."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem Recounted'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem Recounted
      number: 1
      content: "    Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he
        reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hamutal the
        daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        according to all that Jehoiakim had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For because of the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> it came
        to the point in Jerusalem and Judah that he cast them out from his presence.And
        Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And in the ninth year of his reign, in the tenth month, on the tenth
        day of the month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came with all his army against
        Jerusalem, and laid siege to it. And they built siegeworks all around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the city was besieged till the eleventh year of King Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On the ninth day of the fourth month the famine was so severe in
        the city that there was no food for the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then a breach was made in the city, and all the men of war fled and
        went out from the city by night by the way of a gate between the two walls,
        by the king\u2019s garden, and the Chaldeans were around the city. And they
        went in the direction of the Arabah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the army of the Chaldeans pursued the king and overtook Zedekiah
        in the plains of Jericho, and all his army was scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then they captured the king and brought him up to the king of Babylon
        at Riblah in the land of Hamath, and he passed sentence on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The king of Babylon slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes,
        and also slaughtered all the officials of Judah at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Temple Burned'
      title: The Temple Burned
      number: 11
      content: 'He put out the eyes of Zedekiah, and bound him in chains, and the
        king of Babylon took him to Babylon, and put him in prison till the day of
        his death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  In the fifth month, on the tenth day of the month\u2014that was
        the nineteenth year of King Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon\u2014Nebuzaradan
        the captain of the bodyguard, who served the king of Babylon, entered Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he burned the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the
        king\u2019s house and all the houses of Jerusalem; every great house he burned
        down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And all the army of the Chaldeans, who were with the captain of the
        guard, broke down all the walls around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard carried away captive some
        of the poorest of the people and the rest of the people who were left in
        the city and the deserters who had deserted to the king of Babylon, together
        with the rest of the artisans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard left some of the poorest
        of the land to be vinedressers and plowmen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the pillars of bronze that were in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the stands and the bronze sea that were in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the Chaldeans broke in pieces, and carried all the bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And they took away the pots and the shovels and the snuffers and
        the basins and the dishes for incense and all the vessels of bronze used
        in the temple service; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'also the small bowls and the fire pans and the basins and the pots
        and the lampstands and the dishes for incense and the bowls for drink offerings.
        What was of gold the captain of the guard took away as gold, and what was
        of silver, as silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As for the two pillars, the one sea, the twelve bronze bulls that
        were under the sea,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the stands, which Solomon the king
        had made for the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the bronze of
        all these things was beyond weight. '
      comments:
      - number: '52:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As for the pillars, the height of the one pillar was eighteen cubits,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        its circumference was twelve cubits, and its thickness was four fingers,
        and it was hollow. '
      comments:
      - number: '52:21 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'On it was a capital of bronze. The height of the one capital was
        five cubits. A network and pomegranates, all of bronze, were around the capital.
        And the second pillar had the same, with pomegranates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The People Exiled to Babylon'
      title: The People Exiled to Babylon
      number: 23
      content: 'There were ninety-six pomegranates on the sides; all the pomegranates
        were a hundred upon the network all around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest, and Zephaniah
        the second priest and the three keepers of the threshold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "and from the city he took an officer who had been in command of the
        men of war, and seven men of the king\u2019s council, who were found in the
        city; and the secretary of the commander of the army, who mustered the people
        of the land; and sixty men of the people of the land, who were found in the
        midst of the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Nebuzaradan the captain of the guard took them and brought them
        to the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the king of Babylon struck them down and put them to death at
        Riblah in the land of Hamath. So Judah was taken into exile out of its land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the number of the people whom Nebuchadnezzar carried away
        captive: in the seventh year, 3,023 Judeans; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar he carried away captive
        from Jerusalem 832 persons; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Jehoiachin Released from Prison'
      title: Jehoiachin Released from Prison
      number: 30
      content: 'in the twenty-third year of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuzaradan the captain
        of the guard carried away captive of the Judeans 745 persons; all the persons
        were 4,600.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  And in the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin king
        of Judah, in the twelfth month, on the twenty-fifth day of the month, Evil-merodach
        king of Babylon, in the year that he began to reign, graciously freed[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        Jehoiachin king of Judah and brought him out of prison. '
      comments:
      - number: '52:31 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he spoke kindly to him and gave him a seat above the seats of
        the kings who were with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So Jehoiachin put off his prison garments. And every day of his life
        he dined regularly at the king\u2019s table, "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: and for his allowance, a regular allowance was given him by the king,
        according to his daily needs, until the day of his death, as long as he lived.
      comments: []
